(122, 1, 270, 2221, '<p>Mountain biking in Tamil Nadu provides opportunities for scenic voyages through the unventured and underexplored terrains. The sport that is rapidly gaining popularity demands trails and facilities of utmost quality. Tamil Nadu Tourism Development Corporation has set up India&rsquo;s first ever mountain bike park and none other than the Queen of Hill Stations is the ideal location for that. The mountain bike park, established in Ooty as part of a collaborative venture of Tamil Nadu Tourism Development Cooperation and TI Cycles India, provides the riders an astonishing track capable of delivering an enthralling experience regardless of their level of expertise.</p>\r\n<p>The mountain bike park offers four tracks with varying difficulty levels. The Easy level has gentle undulations and enables the riders to cover a riding distance of upto 60 km. The Gentle course with its rolling terrain and occasional moderate and challenging climbs will provide a riding distance of 80 km, and riders with advanced levels of expertise can utilize the Moderate and Challenge courses. The steep ascents and sudden drops of these sections will truly test the mettle of any rider.</p>\r\n<p>Beginners or experts, the track promises everyone a challenging and thrilling experience. Be it a simple tabletop jump or wall ride, the park offers a wide variety of obstacles and challenges, that too without having to disturb even a single tree. The uncompromising safety features, including safety mesh barriers and foam-padded trees, ensure a safe and quality time of enjoyment for everyone. In addition to the mountain bike course, guided Segway tours and activities for kids are also available.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(123, 1, 271, 2228, '<p>You are likely to feel quite at home on an off-roading vehicle when it is out there bashing dunes and slugging out of the slushes. However, the mettle of the explorer in you&nbsp; is tested only when you are in the wild, traversing the uncharted tracks. Tamil Nadu and its diverse landscapes offer countless off-road challenges to those willing to venture into the dirt and test the limits of their muscle strength and machine power.</p>\r\n<p>For off-road junkies, Mahabalipuram is the most favourite destination in Tamil Nadu. A preferred destination for countless off-road drives conducted by various off-road enthusiast groups, Mahabalipuram offers several options for both open and closed terrain drives. Mahabalipuram and its off-drives, conducted throughout the year, pose a variety of challenges like sand, slush, rock and gravel tracks. By enrolling yourself into any of the off-road drives conducted all year round you can be part of an off-road community based around Mahabalipuram with a keen spirit of adventure and healthy sense of camaraderie.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Kolukkumalai Tea Estate is a favourite destination in the Western Ghats for off-road adventures. Kolukkumalai, being the highest tea growing estate, is accessible only via 4-wheel drive vehicles. The treacherous trail winding through the rolling hills of the tea estate is guaranteed to test your persistence and off-roading abilities. A drive that is almost a day long will take you to the top of the estate where you can relax and have a casual stroll around the tea estate.</p>\r\n<p>Javadi Hill is another popular destination for petrolheads to head to if they wish to test their off-road skills. Known as the Ooty of Vellore, Javadi Hill is an extension of the Eastern Ghats and home to several scenic waterfalls and trekking trails. The rocky trails of the hill are ideal spots for a challenging session of rock crawling. There are innumerable attractive spots of scenery that could be set as a final destination of an off-road drive with your buddies. During monsoon season the rocky trails of the hill turn into slush and pose a different challenge to off-roaders.</p>\r\n<p>Step on the gas and venture into the unknown to conquer the never-ending off-road challenges that Tamil Nadu has to offer. Chase the enthralling thrill of bashing the unexplored and cherish the camaraderie that develops along the way.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(124, 1, 272, 2235, '<p>Soar like a bird and float like a butterfly and cherish the ecstasy and fun of flying. Tamil Nadu offers some of the safest parasailing spots in the country that will enable you to savour some of the breathtaking views of its iconic landscapes. Gear up and float away in the sky with wind in your hair. Experience the lightness of a bird and flirt with the clouds while being enchanted by the beauty of the landscape beneath you. Head to any of the parasailing spots across Tamil Nadu and soar like birds with wind in your hair and an aerial view of your favourite destination.</p>\r\n<p>If you are daring enough to venture into the sky, Chennai is where you should head to. With several spots offering parasailing and paramotoring facilities, Chennai has all facilities to help you answer the call of the clouds. Parasailing over Marina Beach is the most popular choice of all. Fly along with seagulls over the crashing waves of the Bay of Bengal with a splendid evening view of sunset and bustling beach beneath you. Chennai has facilities for paramotoring also. Hitch a joyride with trained and certified professionals, and enjoy the thrill and joy of weaving in and out of the clouds like a bird.</p>\r\n<p>Ariyaman Beach in Rameswaram is another destination where one can quench your desire to soar away into clouds like Icarus. The pristine beach on the Palk Bay of Rameshwaram is an underexplored destination that offers numerous adventure activities. Along with wind surfing and boating, the beach has facilities for parasailing over the crashing blue waves of the bay.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
