(168, 1, 223, 1871, NULL, 'Camping in Tamil Nadu| Things to Do in Tamil Nadu', 'camping in tamil nadu, tent camping, ooty camping, camping facilities in tamil nadu, visit tamil nadu, advenure tourism tamil nadu, camp at tamilnadu forests', 'Ooty, being the Queen of Hill Stations, offers countless opportunities for the lovers of nature to explore and wander into the wild and even relish a memorable camping, where one gets to be one with the nature. Innumerable camping spots located in the pristine landscape of Nilgiris make Ooty one of the best camping locations in Tamil Nadu.\r\n\r\n', 'camping', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(169, 1, 224, 1883, NULL, 'Pongal Festival | festivals and Events in Tamil Nadu', 'Pongal, pongal festival, festivals of tamil nadu, major festivals in tamil nadu, pongal speciality, pongal date, pongal festival in english, pongal festival,pongal festival 2022, 5 sentences about pongal festival, pongal festival in tamil, pongal festival images, 10 points about pongal festival in english, pongal festival in hindi, \r\n', 'Pongal is usually celebrated between 13 and 16 January every year.  The four days - Bhogi Pongal, Thai Pongal, Mattu Pongal and Kaanum Pongal - have their significance. Thai Pongal on January 14 corresponds with the Makar Sankranti, the harvest festival.\r\n\r\n', 'pongal-festival', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(170, 1, 225, 1892, NULL, 'Natyanjali Dance Festival', 'Natyanjali Dance Festival, natyanjali dance festival 2022, natyanjali dance festival speciality, application natyanjali dance festival chidambaram, natyanjali dance festival in tamil, natyanjali dance festival pays tribute to which deity ?, natyanjali dance festival in hindi, natyanjali bharatanatyam, natyanjali dance school, chidambaram dance festival, \r\n', 'The Natyanjali Dance Festival falls on Mahashivaratri (festival of Lord Shiva) in the Tamil month of Maasi (between February and March). Natya means âdanceâ and Anjali means âoffering\'\' - the festival of dance offering to God. \r\n\r\n', 'natyanjali-dance-festival', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(171, 1, 226, 1900, NULL, 'Karthigai Deepam | Festivals in Tamil Nadu', 'Karthika festival, karthika deepam, Appa Karthigai, Vada Karthigai, Thiru Karthigai, tamil nadu festivals, \r\n\r\n', 'On Karthigai festival day, kolams or floral patterns are drawn in front of the houses and the houses cleaned and washed.  The doorways are decorated with mango leaf festoons, and oil lamps or agal vilaku are lit. \r\n\r\n', 'karthigai-deepam', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(172, 1, 227, 1908, NULL, 'Jallikattu Bull Festival | Festivals in Tamil Nadu', 'Jallikattu Bull Festival, Jallikattu bull festival, jallikkattu, jallikattu sport, jallikattu festival speciality, jallikattu pongal. jallikattu wikipedia, jallikattu in which state, jallikattu festival is celebrated in which state, jallikattu festival 2022, jallikattu festival date, jallikattu history, sallikkattu,  Mattu Pongal Day\r\n\r\n', 'Jallikattu festival has been a part of cultural tourism activities in the state. Vadi manjuviraá¹­á¹­u, VÄli viraá¹­á¹­u, Vaá¹­am manjuviraá¹­á¹­u are the various variants of this sport. Each version of the sport has different rules. \r\n\r\n', 'jallikattu-bull-festival', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(173, 1, 228, 1916, NULL, 'Music & Dance Festival, Chennai | Festivals in Tamil Nadu', 'chennai music and dance festival, festivals in tamil nadu, chennai dance festivalm', 'The temples and auditoriums in Chennai will reverberate with Ragas and Thalas of music and dance, especially classical music during the months of December and January. Artistes from across the country flock to Chennai to participate in the famous Margazhi festival, that is currently known as the Music and Dance Festival of Chennai. \r\n\r\n', 'music-dance-festival-chennai', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(174, 1, 229, 1924, NULL, 'Vinayaka Chathurthi | Festivals in Tamil Nadu', 'vinayaka chathurthi,', 'Vinayaka Chathurthi is a festival to revere the Lord who removes obstacles, Lord Ganesha. On the fourth day after the new moon in the Tamil month of Avani, devotees start eleven days of celebrations by worshipping clay idols of the Lord. These idols will be installed outdoors in pandals or marquees.\r\n\r\n', 'vinayaka-chathurthi', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
