(204, 1, 275, 2259, NULL, 'Srivilliputhur Sanctuary', 'Srivilliputhur Sanctuary, wildlife sanctuaries in tamil nadu, Andipatti Hills, thirunelveli, places to visit in tamil nadu, must-visit sanctuaries in Tamil Nadu', 'Covering a total area of 485.2 sq.km., Srivilliputhur Sanctuary is bordered by Andipatti Hills in the north and the district of Tirunelveli in the South. Established in the year of 1988 on a mission to conserve the vulnerable Grizzled Giant Squirrel, the sanctuary is home to a number of animals, birds, reptiles and flora of varied species', 'srivilliputhur-sanctuary', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(205, 1, 276, 2274, NULL, 'Guindy National Park', 'Guindy National Park, chennai national park, wildlife sanctuaries in chennai, visit chennai, places to visit in chennai', 'The Guindy National Park is spread over an area of just 2.70 sq.km.. Despite being of a relatively smaller size, it doesnât cease to amaze the visitors in a big way. The park is home to a remarkable assortment of flora and fauna.', 'guindy-national-park', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(206, 1, 277, 2289, NULL, 'Vedanthangal Bird Sanctuary', 'Vedanthangal Bird Sanctuary, bird sanctuaries in tamil nadu, tamil nadu wildlife, wildlife sanctuaries, visit tamil nadu, chengalpattu district, places to visit in tamil nadu', 'Spread across 74 acres of picturesque land in the Chengalpattu district of Tamil Nadu, the Vedanthangal Bird Sanctuary is picture-perfect place for bird watchers and lovers to spend time, observing these flying delights', 'vedanthangal-bird-sanctuary', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(207, 1, 278, 2308, NULL, 'Crocodile Park', 'Crocodile Park, crocodile park in tamil nadu, places to visit in tamil nadu, crocodile park', 'Located just 40 kms to the south of Chennai, the Crocodile Park commenced its operations with a mission to protect three endangered species of crocodiles â the saltwater crocodile, the mugger crocodile and the gharial. These species were nearing extinction at that point and the work of the Crocodile Park was crucial to their survival', 'crocodile-park', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(208, 1, 279, 2324, NULL, 'Nellai Wildlife Sanctuary', 'Nellai wildlife sanctuary, tamil nadu wildlife, sanctuaries in tamil nadu, tamil nasu wild life, national parks, visit tamil nadu, wildlife, wildlife sanctuary in tirunelveli, visit thirunelveli, places to visit in thirunelveli, wildlife safari', 'Nellai Wildlife Sanctuary is one of the newest sanctuaries in Tamil Nadu. It earned the title of wildlife sanctuary in 2015. The sanctuary is located in one of the most beautiful districts in Tamil Nadu â Tirunelveli. What greets a visitor at the Nellai Wildlife Sanctuary is the picturesque landscape of the destination.', 'nellai-wildlife-sanctuary', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(209, 1, 280, 2354, NULL, 'Kumbakarai Falls, Theni', 'Kumbakarai Falls, Theni, waterfalls in theni, waterfalls in tamil nadu, places to visit in theni, kumbakarani waterfalls, kodaikanal, waterfall in kodaikanal, kodaikanal hills, tamil nadu waterfalls', 'Originating in Kodaikanal hills, the Kumbakarani waterfall flows along in stages. The water seems to take a pause in the crevices of wide rock and then it gently meanders down before transforming into a spectacular waterfall from a steep rock.', 'kumbakarai-falls', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(210, 1, 281, 2370, NULL, 'Suruli Falls, Theni', 'Suruli falls theni, waterfalls in theni, waterfalls in tamil nadu, meghamalai, places to visit in tamil nadu, waterfalls', 'Suruli Waterfalls originates from the picturesque Meghamalai. The place is as much known for its scenic beauty as for the flawless manner in which it is maintained. Be rest assured of a safe bathing spot, railings, well maintained change rooms and rest rooms here. ', 'suruli-falls-theni', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(211, 1, 282, 2391, NULL, 'Megam Falls | Waterfalls in Tamil Nadu | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Meghamalai, meghamalai waterfalls, kallakurichi, megam waterfalls, waterfalls in tamil nadu, tamil nadu tourism, places to visit in tamil nadu, trekking to megamalai, kalrayan hills, waterfalls in theni, chinna suruli falls, ', 'One among the most beautiful waterfalls, Megamalai situated in Theni is a must visit destination in Tamil Nadu. ', 'megam-falls', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(212, 1, 283, 2407, NULL, 'Navratri Festivals | Festival & Events | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'navratri, navarathri, navarathri festival, festivals in tamil nadu, golu making, navarathri golu, festival of lishts, tamil nadu tourism, ', 'Navratri is one of the most popular festivals in Tamil Nadu. People in the State decorate their houses to welcome the three Goddesses, Durga, Saraswati, and Lakshmi. The festival begins along with Devi Paksha which falls in the Ashwin month (September -October) and ends with the Vijayadashami. ', 'navratri', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(213, 1, 284, 2415, NULL, 'Deepavali | Festivals & Events | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'deepawali, diwali, depavali festival, festivals and events, festivals in tamil nadu, ', 'The term Deepavali is formed by coining the Sanskrit words, Deep (lamp) and vali (array). In Tamil Nadu, the five-day Deepavali celebrations begin with an oil bath before sunrise. This is considered akin to taking bath in the Ganges.', 'deepavali', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(214, 1, 285, 2423, NULL, 'Saraswathi Pooja | Festivals & Events | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'saraswathi pooja, ayur pooja, astra pooja, festivals and events in tamil nadu, navarathri, vijayadashmi, mahanavami, ', 'During the evening of Mahanavami, the Goddess of wisdom, art, and literature is revered by keeping the books, instruments, and tools are kept for Puja in front of the idol of Goddess Saraswati (in the Golu/Kolu display) and this remains untouched until the next day â Vijayadasami day.', 'saraswathi-pooja', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(215, 1, 286, 2431, NULL, 'Chithirai | Festivals & Events | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Chitri Rai Festival, Chithirai, Chithirai Thiruvizha, Meenakshi Thirukalyanam, Meenakshi Kalyanam, festivals in tamil nadu, tamil nadu tourism', 'Chithirai festival also known as Chithirai Thiruvizha, Meenakshi Thirukalyanam or Meenakshi Kalyanam falls at the beginning of April or the Tamil month Chithirai. It is a 15 days celebration that brings harmony to everyone irrespective of caste and religion. The festival also sees a union between the two Hindu sects, Shaivites and Vaishnavites, devotees of Shiva and Vishnu respectively.', 'chithirai', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(216, 1, 287, 2439, NULL, 'Pine Forest | Places to Visit | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'pine forest ooty, places to visit in ooty, pine forest shooting location, ooty shooting locations, pine tree forest, tamil nadu tourism', 'Nestled in the slopes of Nilgiris, the Pine Tree Forest is a grove of orderly growing pine trees that are several hundreds of years old. These ancient woods are home to a wide variety of fauna, ranging from fluttering butterflies that delight the air to wild goats that roam the woods.', 'pine-forest', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(217, 1, 288, 2455, NULL, 'Lake Park, ooty | Tourist Destinations | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'lake park, tamil nadu tourism, tourist destinations in ooty, places to visit in ooty, ooty lake, ', 'The Lake Park, as the name suggests, is located on the banks of the Ooty Lake. It is the perfect place to laze around and spend a leisurely day in, and is located in the city centre just opposite the railway station and very near the bus terminus. ', 'lake-park', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(218, 1, 289, 2471, NULL, 'Deer Park, Ooty | Tourist Destinations | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'ooty, deer park ooty, places to visit in ooty, deer park, tamil nadu tourism', 'The Sambar and Chital species of deer can be found in the park. The Deer Park in Ooty is a haven for Nature lovers as it is wrapped in a chilly climate and surrounded by enticing flora and fauna. ', 'deer-park-ooty', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(219, 1, 290, 2487, NULL, 'Government Museum Ooty | Tourist destinations | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'government museum, places to visit in ooty, ooty museum tamil nadu tourism', 'The Government Museum in Ooty, situated on the Ooty-Mysore Road, gives a peek into the culture and ancient heritage of the tribes of Ooty. The Museum is also known as the Stone house or the Kal bungalow by the locals.', 'government-museum-ooty', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(220, 1, 291, 2503, NULL, 'Chennai | Capital City | Metropolis | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'chennai, ', 'Chennai is often referred to as the Detroit of India because of the presence of a thriving automobile sector. Chennai is also home to many major industries that add significantly to the financial growth of India. Lately Chennai has also risen in ranks as one of the most promising IT destinations in India. Once the capital of South Indian cinema, today Chennai is home to the Tamil Film industry that has viewers all over the world. ', 'chennai', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
