(226, 1, 297, 2589, NULL, 'Dhanushkodi Beach  | Destinations | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'dhanushkodi beach, beaches in tamil nadu, dhanushkodi, Dhanushkodi beach, beaches in tamil nadu, dhanuskodi, places to visit in danushkodi, tamil nadu tourism, tourist places in tamil nadu, rameswaram, pamapan bridge, gulf of mannar, places to visit in ramewsaram, dhanushkodi trip, danushkodi tourism, ', 'The word Dhanushkodi means âTip of the bowâ. âArichal Munaiâ is the point at which the Indian Ocean meets the Bay of Bengal and the spot can be viewed from Dhanushkodi. This pristine beach is surrounded by the Gulf of Mannar on one side and the Bay of Bengal on the other', 'dhanuskodi-beach', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(227, 1, 298, 2605, NULL, 'Coutrallam Waterfalls | Destinations | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'coutrallam, kuttalam, kutrallam, waterfalls, thenkasi waterfalls, places to visit in thenkasi, tenkasi tourism, kutrallam waterfalls trip, places to visit in tamil nadu, palaruv falls, tiger falls, Main Falls, Peraruvi, Small Falls, Chittaruvi, Chembakadevi, Shenbaga Falls, Honey Falls, Thenaruvi, Five Falls, Aintharuvi, Tiger Falls, Puliaruvi, Old Coutrallam Falls, Pazhaya Courtallam, New Fall, Puthu Aruvi, Fruit Garden Falls Orchard Falls, Pazhathotta Arvui ', 'Fed by the River Chittra, Manimutharu, Pachaiyar and Tamirabarani the waterfall cascades over 60m-92 m. Main Falls (Peraruvi), Small Falls (Chittaruvi), Chembakadevi (Shenbaga) Falls, Honey Falls (Thenaruvi), Five Falls (Aintharuvi), Tiger Falls (Puliaruvi), Old Courtallam Falls (Pazhaya Courtallam), New Falls (Puthu Aruvi), Fruit Garden Falls or Orchard Falls (Pazhathotta Arvui) are the nine falls and each one offers a different experience in terms of volume and height', 'coutrallam-waterfalls', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(228, 1, 299, 2621, NULL, 'Manimuthar Falls | Destinations | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Manimuthar Falls, waterfalls in thirunelveli, places to vissit in tirunelveli, tamil nadu tourism, \r\n', 'Located near Manjolai hills in Tirnelveli district, River Manimuthar feeds this waterfall. The pristine beauty of this place is amplified by the natural waterfall. Nearby lies a pond, adding to the appeal. Take a short drive along the Ghat road from Manimuthar dam and you reach this beautiful place. The water flows from a height of 25 feet and falls into the pond.', 'manimuthar-falls', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(229, 1, 300, 2637, NULL, 'Papanasam Agasthiyar Falls  destinations | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Papanasam Agasthiyar Falls, waterfalls in tamil nadu, ', 'The natural beauty and the beliefs surrounding this place make it a popular destination for tourists and pilgrims. A 3 km trek leads you to Papanasam waterfalls. Being close to the forests, tourists get to spot wild animals most often and the place is located near the Kalakkad - Mundanthurai tiger reserve. The place is abound in legends. ', 'papanasam-agasthiyar-falls', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(230, 1, 301, 2651, NULL, 'The Kapaleeshwarar Temple | Temples of Chennai | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'The Kapaleshwarar Temple, Tamil Nadu tourism, temples in south india, temples of Chennai, siva temples in india, dravidian architecture, The Kapaleshwarar Temple, Mylapore, Tamil Nadu tourism, temples in Chennai, temples in south india, Kapaleeshwarar ', 'The Kapaleshwarar Temple in Mylapore is an old shrine, dedicated to Lord Shiva. Built in the 7th century, the temple boasts an impressive Dravidian architecture where devotees throng in large numbers throughout the year.', 'the-kapaleeshwarar-temple', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(231, 1, 305, 2674, NULL, 'Sri Parthasarathy Temple | Temples in Chennai | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Sri Parthasarathy Temple, Temples in Chennai, Tamil Nadu Tourism, Dravidian architecture', 'The Parthasarathy Temple at Triplicane in Chennai was built in the 8th century AD by the rulers of the Pallava Dynasty with later addition by the Cholas and the Vijaynagar Empire. An ultimate example of Dravidian architecture, the myriad Tamil and Telugu inscriptions on the temple are worth noting.', 'sri-parthasarathy-temple', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(232, 1, 308, 2695, NULL, 'Hogenakkal Waterfalls | Destinations  | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'hogenakkal, coracle rafting in hogenakkal, hogenakkal boating, dharmapuri waterfalls, must visit destinations in tamil nadu, tamil nadu tourism, ', 'Hogenakkal is one of the most celebrated waterfalls in Tamil Nadu. The water falling at a high speed then merges into Mettur Stanley reservoir. The dam constructed in 1939 is used for irrigation and hydropower generation.', 'hogenakkal-waterfalls', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(233, 1, 309, 2709, NULL, 'Tirumala Tirupathi Devasthanam | Temples of Chennai | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'tirumala tirupathi devasthanam, temples of Chennai, tamil nadu tourism', 'Located in T Nagar, the Tirumala Tirupathi Devasthanam is a popular religious shrine highly regarded by the Tamilians. ', 'tirumala-tirupathi-devasthanam', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(234, 1, 310, 2722, NULL, 'San Thome Cathedral Basilica | Churches in Chennai | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'San Thome Cathedral Basilica, Churches in Chennai, tamil Nadu Tourism', 'San Thome Church, is known as St. Thomas Cathedral Basilica and National Shrine of Saint Thomas, is a Catholic minor basilica in the Santhome neighbourhood of Chennai, the capital city of Tamil Nadu, India.', 'san-thome-cathedral-basilica', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(235, 1, 311, 2735, NULL, 'Sri Ramkrishna Math | Spiritual Centres in Chennai | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Sri Ramkrishna Math, Spiritual Centres in Chennai, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Sri Ramkrishna Math in Chennai is dedicated to the famous saint and religious reformer, Ramakrishna Paramhansa. The temple was founded in 1897 by Swami Ramakrishnananda, a direct disciple of the former who came to Chennai to spread his guru\'s message. It has the idols of Sri Ramakrishna Paramhansa, Sri Sarada Devi and Swami Vivekananda. ', 'sri-ramkrishna-math', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(236, 1, 312, 2750, NULL, 'Kutladampatti Falls, Madurai | Destinations | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Kutladampatti Falls, Madurai, tamil nadu tourism', 'If you are looking for a less crowded but beautiful picnic spot, head to Kutladampatti waterfalls. Located in Cholavantha village near Madurai, this is located inside the reserve forest of Kutladampatti. Bask yourself in the quietness of nature interrupted by the medley of lovely sounds of nature and the gentle cascading waterfalls. ', 'kutladampatti-falls', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(237, 1, 316, 2778, NULL, 'Puliyancholai Falls | Destinations | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Puliyancholai Falls, Thrichy, waterfalls in tamil nadu, places to visist in thrichy, thrichy tourism, tamil nadu tourism, trichy, namakkal tourism, places to visit in namakkal', 'Puliyancholai waterfalls in Trichy offers immense possibilities for trekking and adventurous activities.  You can\'t ask for a better place, if you love nature and travel. Explore the forest and take a nice walk to discover herbs.', 'puliyancholai-falls', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(238, 1, 317, 2794, NULL, 'Kanyakumari | Cities of Tamil Nadu | Pilgrim city | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'kanyakumari, district, kanyakumari beach, vivekananda rock, kanyakumari temple, places to visit in kanyakumari, kanyakumari beach, kanyakumari hotels, kanyakumari temple, cape comorin, kumari, kumari munai, coastal town in tamil nadu, southernmost point of peninsular india, thiruvalluvar statue, vivekananda rock memorial', 'The place gets its name from the Hindu goddess Devi Kanyakumari, who is considered to be the sister of Lord Krishna. ', 'kanyakumari', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(239, 1, 318, 2809, NULL, 'Vaidehi Waterfalls | Destinations | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'vaidehi waterfalls, waterfalls in tamil nadu, tamil nadu tourism, narasihapuram, ', 'Located in Narasimhapuram village, the walk to Vaidehi falls is exciting. Gear up for a calming stroll, listening to the chirping of birds and faint, distant sounds emanating from deep inside the forest. As you get closer, your ears open up to the gentle gurgle of water which slowly transforms to the sound of gushing water.', 'vaidehi-waterfalls', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(240, 1, 319, 2825, NULL, 'Catherine Waterfalls | Destinations | Tamil Nadu tourism', 'Catherine Waterfalls, kotagiri, nilgiris, waterfalls in nilgiris, tamil nadu tourism, ', 'Located in Kotagiri in Nilgiri district, Catherine waterfall has a  curious name. It is named after the wife of M D Cockburn, a Scottish planter who introduced coffee, pears and apple plantation in the hill stations. The water cascades from a height of 76.2 m and leaves you in awe.', 'catherine-waterfalls', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(241, 1, 320, 2841, NULL, 'Kancheepuram | Golden City of a Thousand Temples | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'kanchipuram, kancheepuram, places to visit in tamil nadu tamil handloom, kanchipattu, kancheepuram village in tamil nadu, kanchipuram temple, places to visit in kanchipuram, things to do in kanchipuram, golden city of a thousand temples, district', 'Kancheepuram is such a special town that takes you back in time and drench you with its old-world charm and cultural richness. ', 'kancheepuram', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(242, 1, 321, 2857, NULL, 'Thanjavur | Cities of Tamil Nadu | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'thanjavur, thanjavur temple, places to visit in thanjavur, thanjvur tourism, thanjavur tourist places, thanjavur famous things to buy, places to visit in thanjavur other than temples, thanjavur tourist places in tamil, thanjavur famous food, waterfalls near thanjavur, hill stations near thanjavur, romantic places in thanjavur, Great Living Chola Temples', 'Arrive at the destination and be wondered about the breadth of lush green paddy fields that offer an absolute feast to the eyes. ', 'thanjavur', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(243, 1, 322, 2873, NULL, 'Salem | Cities of Tamil Nadu | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'salem, plantations in salem, places to visit in salem, salem trip, jeragamalai, nagaramalai, godumalai, kanjanamalai hills, thirumanimutharu lake, tamil nadu, places to visit in tamil nadu', 'On the banks of Thirumanimutharu Lake lies the serene city of Salem, one of the largest urban agglomerations in Tamil Nadu. A fast-growing centre for trade, industries and other commercial activities, Salem is a naturally blessed district surrounded by lush greenery and hills. ', 'salem', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(244, 1, 323, 2889, NULL, 'Thalaiyar Waterfalls | Destinations | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Thalaiyar Waterfalls, waterfalls in tamil nadu, tamil nadu tourism, dindigul, ', 'Located in the Palani hills of Dindugul district, Thalaiyar is the highest waterfall in Tamilnadu. The 975 ft high waterfall makes for an exhilirating sight. For all the marvellous beauty of this waterfall, accessing the place won\'t be everybody\'s cup of tea. ', 'thalaiyar-waterfalls', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(245, 1, 324, 2905, NULL, 'Monkey Waterfalls | Destinations | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Monkey Waterfalls, Coimbatore', 'Located in the uphill Ghat road on the Pollachi-Valparai road in the Anaimalai hill range, Monkey waterfalls is known for the quiet, scenic splendour and the enchanting calmness surrounding the area. Water gushes down from a height of around 18 metres and makes for a scintillating sight', 'monkey-waterfalls', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(246, 1, 325, 2921, NULL, 'Agni Theertham Beach | Beaches in Rameswaram | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Agni Theertham Beach, Agni theertham beach in tamil nadu, beaches in tamil nadu, tamil nadu tourism, rameswaram, dhanushkodi, ramanathapuram, places to visit in ramanathapuram, beaches in rameswaram, ', 'Agni Theertham is a beach in Rameshwaram that will fascinate you with such a story from the great Indian epic of Ramayana. The beach is also a popular spot for tourists to enjoy the golden sands and tides that only a pristine seashore can assure you.', 'agni-theertham-beach', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(247, 1, 326, 2935, NULL, 'Thiruparappu | Waterfalls | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Thirparappu Falls', 'The cascading falls of the Thirparappu Falls in Kanyakumari district make for an enchanting sight to behold. The waterfall originates at the Kodyar River and descends at Thirparappu from a height of around 50 feet. ', 'thirparappu-falls', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(248, 1, 327, 2948, NULL, 'Vattakottai Fort | Kanyakumari | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Vattakottai Fort, Kanyakumari,  Tamil Nadu Tourism, Travancore Kingdom, forts in tamil nadu, places to visit, things to do in kanyakumari, monuments, ', 'The Vattakotai Fort is a must-visit attraction on Kanyakumari. It is one of the last coastal forts constructed by the rulers of the Travancore Kingdom. Built of solid stone, the fort comprises watch towers, weapon rooms and resting rooms. ', 'vattakottai-fort', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(249, 1, 328, 2961, NULL, 'Sothavilai Beach | Kanyakumari | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Sothavilai Beach, Kanyakumari, Tamil Nadu tourism, beaches in kanyakumari, kanyakumari district, places to visit in kanyakumari, things to do in kanyakumari, visit kanyakumari, tamil nadu tourism, ', 'Sothavilai Beach, in Kanyakumari district, is one of the longest natural sandy beaches in South India. A walk along the Sothavilai Beach during sunset would be an experience of a lifetime. ', 'sothavilai-beach', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(250, 1, 329, 2974, NULL, 'Padmanabhapuram Palace | Kanyakumari | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Padmanabhapuram Palace, thackalay kottaram, palaces in tamil nadu, travancore dynasty, kanyakumari trip, places to visit in kanyakumari, visit tamil nadu, tamil nadu tourism, royal houses, Veli Hills, Kulasekhara Perumal, travancore kingdom, ', 'The Padmanabhapuram Palace located at the foothills of the Veli Hills in Kanyakumari district was built in the 16th century by Kulasekhara Perumal of the Travancore Kingdom. ', 'padmanabhapuram-palace', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(251, 1, 330, 2989, NULL, 'Muthu Nagar Beach | Destinations  Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Muthu Nagar Beach, thoothukudi, tuticorin, beaches in thoothukudi, places to visit in thoothukudi, tamil nadu tourism', 'One of the most picturesque beach destinations in Tamil Nadu, Muthu Nagar beach is a perfect package of fun, leisure and adventure. The sunset view from the beach is astounding and this makes the location a much sought-after spot for various kinds of activities including photography.', 'muthu-nagar-beach', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(252, 1, 331, 3003, NULL, 'Mathoor Aqueduct | Hanging Bridge in Kanyakumari | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Mathoor Aqueduct, Mathur Aqueduct, Kanyakumari, Tamil Nadu tourism', 'The Mathoor Aqueduct in Kanyakumari, measuring one kilometre in length and 115 feet in height, is one of the tallest and the longest trough bridges in Asia. The hanging bridge, an imposing structure was constructed in 1966 over the Pahrali River and till date attracts a lot of tourists. ', 'mathoor-aqueduct', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(253, 1, 332, 3016, NULL, 'The Isha Yoga Center | Adi Yogi Siva | Pilgrim Centre | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'The Isha Yoga Center, Adi Yogi Siva, Pilgrim Centre, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'The Isha Yoga Center situated at the foothills of Velliangiri, on the outskirts of Coimbatore, is the headquarters for Isha Foundation. Isha is a sacred space for self-transformation, where you can come dedicate time towards your inner growth.', 'the-isha-yoga-center ', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(254, 1, 333, 3029, NULL, 'Gandhi Memorial Mandapam | Kanyakumari | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Gandhi Memorial Mandapam', 'The Gandhi Memorial, built in memory of the Father of the Nation, is yet another major tourist attraction in Kanyakumari. After his death, his ashes were immersed in the Triveni Sangam, here in Kanyakumari. The architecture of the memorial closely resembles Hindu Shrines of Central India. Which is why man address it as the Gandhi Mandapam.', 'gandhi-memorial-mandapam', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(255, 1, 334, 3042, NULL, 'Chitharal Jain Rock Cut Temple | Kanyakumari | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Chitharal Jain Rock Cut Temple, Chitharal Malai Kovil, Chitharal Village, Jain architecture, Thirucharanathu Bhataariyar, Mahavira', 'Chitharal Jain Rock Cut Temple, also known as Chitharal Malai Kovil, Chitharal Cave Temple or Bhagawathi Temple, is located near Chitharal Village in Kanyakumari district, Tamil Nadu, India. It upholds a typical Jain architecture and the entry is through a cave that contains rock-cut sculptures of the Jain Tirthankaras. The presiding deity here happens to be Thirucharanathu Bhataariyar. The idol of Mahavira is also installed in the cave.', 'chitharal-jain-rock-cut-temple', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
