(291, 1, 371, 3548, NULL, 'Pykara | Ooty | The Nilgiris | Tamil Nadu Toursim', 'Pykara, Ooty, pykara waterfalls, pykara hills, ooty, places to visit in ooty, tourist destinations in ooty, ooty tourism, vsit ooty, pykara, tamil nadu tourism, tourist destinations in tamil nadu, ', 'Pykara, OotyOriginating from the heights of Mukurthi Hills, Pykara river cuts through the misty heights of Nilgiris and navigates itself to the rolling green hills and valleys, creating some of the most picturesque views in Ooty. Revered by the locals as a sacred river, the untouched landscapes carved by the Pykara offers an enchanting experience to a soul in search of tranquillity.', 'pykara-ooty', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(292, 1, 372, 3562, NULL, 'Rameswaram Temple | Ramanathapuram District | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Rameswaram Temple, Ramanathapuram District, Tamil Nadu Tourism, Ramanathaswamy Temple, most famous temple in tamil nadu, tamil nadu toursm, rameswaram pilgrimage, dhanushkodi, rameswaram beach, ', 'Ramanathaswamy Temple or Rameswaram Temple is a Hindu temple dedicated to the god Shiva located on Rameswaram island in Ramanathapuram District in Tamil Nadu, India. It is also one of the twelve Jyotirlinga temples. The primary deity of the temple is Ramanathaswamy (Shiva) in the form of lingam. It is considered a holy pilgrimage site for Shaivites, Vaishnavites and Smarthas.', 'rameswaram-temple', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1);
