(64, 1, 108, 983, 'Here, hymns and chants fill the air, creating a mesmerizingly hallowed ambiance. As the sea waves rise, so do the emotions in the minds of millions of devotees. Rameswaram is a vibrant destination, so divine and so very poetic.', 1),
(65, 1, 109, 998, 'Thereâs a world under the ocean, so breathtaking and so vivid; one that needs all of us to step up in order to be protected. Gulf of Mannar Marine National Park is all about preserving the rich biodiversity of the deep blue sea.', 1),
(66, 1, 110, 1013, 'A quiet farm town blessed with lush green landscapes, Kallakurichi retains an old rustic charm. Even with its village like character, this is a well connected place being in the middle of Chennai-Salem National Highways. With its lush greenery and presence of tourist spots with a rich history, Kallakurichi gives a lot to discover', 1),
(67, 1, 111, 1028, 'Karur has an old world charm about it and blends well with its status as an established industrial centre. The city is known for its cottage and handloom industry. Being one of the oldest towns in the city, exploring Karur will offer up slices of history in all its glory.', 1),
(68, 1, 112, 1043, 'Right from the origin of its name, Mayiladuthurai has an inexorable connect with the myths and history. The name originates from the legend that Goddess Parvathi took the form of a peacock to solicit the attention of Lord Shiva', 1),
(69, 1, 113, 1058, 'Namakkal is one city where you get to experience the urban vibes and the rustic charm. A fast developing city, it packs a punch for the tourists with the collection of historic temples, scenic locations and dam sites. Experience the well developed infrastructure at Namakkal which is also famous as an industrial hub. ', 1),
(70, 1, 114, 1073, 'From temples that retell the legacy dating back to centuries to imposing dams, Perambalur offers a lot to explore.', 1),
(71, 1, 115, 1088, 'Pudukottai has a laid back charm and tucked away in this quiet town are the remnants of centuries old civilization. Explore this town a bit and you will step into the glorious world of art, culture and civilization. Pudukottai still carries the legacy of ancient towns, rock cut cave temples, paintings and it is not a surprise that Pudukottai never ceases to catch the fancy of a tourist and a history buff alike.  ', 1),
(72, 1, 137, 1222, 'Itâs more than a national park. Itâs a treasure trove of fascinating experiences that will surprise you beyond bounds. From jungle adventures to trekking trails and more, the Mukurthi National Park offers visitors spectacular treats that they will totally love.', 1),
(73, 1, 138, 1237, 'What a majestic sight it will be, as you go deep into the jungle, hearing the mumbling growl of one of the most beautiful beasts on the planet; and to see it walk past you, like the boss it really is.', 1),
(74, 1, 139, 1252, 'Miles and miles of mind-blowing greenery that creates an ideal ecosystem, and a variety of flora and fauna that thrives on the coziness of this shade that Nature has created for them; Kalakad Mundanthurai Tiger Reserve is indeed a haven for wildlife.', 1),
(75, 1, 140, 1267, 'Just like the enthralling grace of a dancing peacock, this locale is filled with natural beauty that will fill your mind with joy. Itâs a safe haven for beautiful species of wildlife and an awesome retreat for visitors who wish to see the grace of nature.', 1),
(76, 1, 141, 1282, 'Chettinadu cuisine is a delectable combination of heady spices and subtle flavours that shoots straight to your heart right from the very first bite. Distinct aromas and vivid flavours make it a culinary masterpiece.', 1),
(77, 1, 142, 1292, 'Experience a delightful journey through the indigenous spices of the Kongu region of Tamil Nadu. Kongunadu cuisine brings you back to the simpler times of primal flavours from Tamil Naduâs heartlands. ', 1),
(78, 1, 143, 1302, 'Nanjil Nadu cuisine is a delicious blend of the rich culinary traditions of Tamil Nadu and Kerala that you can experience in the southernmost tip of India. It conveys the flavours of these adjacent states with its copious use of coconut and coconut oil.', 1),
(79, 1, 145, 1319, 'Relish the royal flavours of Tamil Nadu, that date back to the reign of the Pandya kings. Explore the unparalleled assortment of traditional dishes marked by its spicy and tangy flavours.   ', 1),
(80, 1, 146, 1329, 'The cuisine of Thanjavur is a mix of traditional Brahmin, Mukkulathor and Maratha cuisines, drawing from the communities that have lived in and around the area. The Maratha dynasty which ruled from 1674 -1855 AD had heavily influenced the cuisine of this region.', 1),
(203, 1, 532, 5101, 'The Mudaliars were historically rich farmers or the agriculturalists who had made many breakthroughs in the field of agriculture. They are also flushed with money (mudra) perhaps, from where the word Mudaliars had come into existence.', 1),
(81, 1, 147, 1339, 'With their incredible hospitality, itâs no surprise that a few temples in Tamil Nadu painstakingly keep up the tradition of feeding their devotees as well as travellers visiting the temple with scrumptious delights. The food provided at the temples in Tamil Nadu have been almost developed into a brand, with mouth-watering offerings made to God.', 1),
(82, 1, 148, 1349, 'Biriyani tops any food loverâs list of favourite dishes, and itâs more than just comfort food. Many states in India have their own style of preparation but the biriyanis of Tamil Nadu are absolutely drool-worthy, enticing people with a melange of tempting flavours.', 1),
(83, 1, 149, 1359, 'Chettinad chicken curry is one of the best ways to cook chicken in a blend of all the authentic Chettinad spices. This aromatic dish is the flag bearer of the Chettinad cuisine made of freshly ground spices along with generous portions of shallots, tomatoes, ginger, chillies and coconut. The spicy and fiery Chettinad chicken curry is served with ghee rice, idli, dosa, idiyappam, appam, etc.', 1),
(84, 1, 150, 1369, 'Karaikudi Prawn masala is another flavourful dish from Chettinad cuisine, a dish that no seafood lover should ever miss! This Chettinad prawn masala is easy to prepare, and the sweet prawns blend well with the heady Chettinad spices. The Karaikudi Prawn masala is finger-licking good and is served best with steamed rice or porotta.', 1),
(85, 1, 151, 1379, 'Chettinad Kuzhi Paniyaram is a popular snack in Tamil Nadu which is also served as breakfast/dinner with sambar or chutney as a side dish. There is no better way to put the leftover idli/dosa batter to better use than by making super soft and fluffy paniyarams. The authentic Chettinad Kuzhi Paniyaram is easy to make, and is sure to be a favourite evening snack for children.', 1),
(86, 1, 152, 1389, 'The Chettinad Uppu Kozhukkattai is an easy evening snack and traditional dish made of rice flour. Since Kozhukkattai is a steamed dish, it is a healthy alternative to fried snack items, perfect for children and health freaks.', 1),
(87, 1, 153, 1399, 'The flavourful and spicy Chettinad Urulai roast or potato fry is an easy and quickly-made side dish that has all the authentic flavours found in Chettinad recipes. Urulai roast goes well with almost anything but is best eaten with rice in South Indian meals. The dish is made using freshly-ground spices and elevates any ordinary meal to a delightful experience.', 1),
(88, 1, 154, 1409, 'The Ulundhu Kali is a traditional Tamil sweet dish that is made using generous amounts of gingelly oil and palm jaggery (karupatti in Tamil). The dish is considered extremely healthy and full of protein, and is a preferred item in the diet of pregnant women to strengthen their bones and improve digestion. This highly nutritious dish from the Kongunadu cuisine can be eaten as an evening snack and is loaded with health benefits.  ', 1),
(89, 1, 155, 1419, 'Kambu dosa or Millet dosa made using pearl millets is a healthy and delicious dish that contains a good amount of protein, carbs, minerals and iron. For those keen on including healthier alternatives to rice, Kambu dosa is an ideal dish for breakfast or dinner. This traditional recipe is easy to make, is believed to keep blood sugar under control and is loaded with nutrients.', 1),
(90, 1, 156, 1429, 'Fritters made using banana blossom/ banana flower, known as Vazhaipoo Vadai in Tamil, is a scrumptious snack and traditional recipe from the Kongunadu region of Tamil Nadu. The crisp Vazhaipoo Vadai goes best with rasam saadam (rasam rice) or as an evening snack with tea or coffee', 1),
(91, 1, 157, 1439, 'This simple one-pot dish, one of the signature dishes from the Kongunadu region, is known for its easy cooking procedure and health benefits. This mix of rice and dal is a yummy combination that can be made in a jiffy and is an ideal lunch box recipe on a busy day.', 1),
(92, 1, 158, 1449, 'Elaneer Payasam is a delicious dessert unique to the Kondunadu cuisine, which is made using tender coconut. The Elaneer payasam is rich and creamy and is mostly served chill. Like many Kongu dishes, the Elaneer Payasam is also nutritious and has a unique texture that has tender coconut bits to bite.', 1),
(93, 1, 195, 1684, 'A quaint air of spirituality pervades the town of Sivagangai. Dotted with temples built during the ancient times, Sivaganga is rooted in Tamil tradition. For a traveller, it is a place worth exploring and more than the temples, the town is also known for its sanctuary and palaces.', 1),
(94, 1, 196, 1699, 'History comes alive in all its glory at Thiruvarur. A prominent and most frequented hub of religious tourism, Thiruvarur serves multifarious experiences for the tourists as well as the pilgrims. For the music lovers and the culture lovers, the place is even more special as Tiruvarur is the birthplace of the great Music Trinity Sri Thagaraja Swamigal, Sri Shyama Sastrigal and Sri Muthuswamy Dikshitar.', 1),
(95, 1, 197, 1714, 'Urban vibes blend seamlessly with the rich heritage in Thiruchirappalli. Embrace the best of both worlds in this city where thriving infrastructure weds a glorious past. Explore the historic temples, cathedrals, butterfly park and take home some wonderful memories', 1),
(96, 1, 198, 1729, 'Isn\'t it just wonderful that we don\'t expect too much of a place and all of a sudden it starts serving up such warm surprises. Well, Tirupathur is one such place. A low key, calm town, Tirupathur is fast emerging as a beautiful tourist destination. ', 1),
(97, 1, 199, 1744, 'A buzzing industrial hub, Tiruppur teems with a multitude of options for tourists. Dotted with dams, stone sculptures, historic temples and wildlife sanctuaries, Tiruppur has something for everyone. You just need to chart your trip and explore it to the fullest.', 1),
(98, 1, 224, 1876, 'If you happen to be in Tamil Nadu by mid-January, and see places squeaky clean, people all decked up in new clothes and ordering fresh belongings, animals smeared with sandalwood paste and cleaned up, do not be surprised.  The state is getting ready to celebrate its much awaited Pongal festival. \r\n', 1),
(99, 1, 225, 1885, 'Imagine more than 7,000 dancers performing dance in a single venue for about 14 minutes! That too at the same time. This extravagant and mesmerising performance took place in the temple of Lord Shiva, the Cosmic Dancer, in the Chidambara Nataraja Temple in Cuddalore in 2019 as part of Tamil Naduâs annual dance festival, Natyanjali and entered the Guinness Book of World Records.\r\n', 1),
(100, 1, 226, 1894, 'Only a full moon can match the radiance of a whole state when it lights clay oil lamps or agal vilaku on the night of Karthigai festival. To ward off evil spirits, Karthigai Deepam, (Karthikeya is Lord Muruga) has been celebrated in Tamil Nadu since the Sangam Age (200 BCE - 300 CE). The songs of Avaiyyar, one of the ancient poets, also mention this festival of lights.\r\n\r\n', 1),
(101, 1, 227, 1902, 'The Tamil annual festival, Pongal has more vigour in districts like Madurai, Pudukottai, Tiruchirapalli and Tanjavur for it hosts the famous and ancient sports festival - Jallikattu. The bullfight that is similar to the Spanish bullfights traces its history to around 2000 years when the fight was conducted to select the most suitable bridegroom. \r\n', 1),
(102, 1, 228, 1910, 'The temples and auditoriums in Chennai will reverberate with Ragas and Thalas of music and dance, especially classical music during the months of December and January. Artistes from across the country flock to Chennai to participate in the famous Margazhi festival, that is currently known as the Music and Dance Festival of Chennai. \r\n\r\n', 1),
(103, 1, 229, 1918, 'Vinayaka Chathurthi is a festival to revere the Lord who removes obstacles, Lord Ganesha. On the fourth day after the new moon in the Tamil month of Avani, devotees start eleven days of celebrations by worshipping clay idols of the Lord. These idols will be installed outdoors in pandals or marquees.\r\n\r\n', 1),
(104, 1, 231, 1935, 'The picturesque Ooty Lake, also known as the Ooty boat house, is a much sought-after tourist attraction located in the midst of serene greenery. The Ooty Lake is an artificially constructed lake, built by John Sullivan in 1824. ', 1),
(105, 1, 248, 2093, 'Discover the perfect mix of history, heritage, beautiful sights and shopping in one of the most loved tourist locations in Tamilnadu; Vellore. Here you can find yourself marveling at the historic sites that carry the rich legacy of the past. Pick your way through the bustle of the famous shopping streets in Vellore and get something nice and beautiful to take home.', 1),
(106, 1, 249, 2109, 'This city boasts of high connectivity and packs in a wide array of tourist attractions. From the historic sites to centuries old pilgrimage spots, Villupuram gives plenty of options to explore the place in its entirety. ', 1),
(107, 1, 250, 2125, 'If you happen to be a foodie and traveller, fewer places could match Virudhunagar to match your taste for excellent cuisine and great places. Packed with wonderful tourist spots, Virudhunagar is an ideal combo of scenic charm and religious sites. Add to it, a unique shopping experience, you get a lovely picture of this remarkable place. ', 1),
(108, 1, 275, 2254, 'Deep into the wilderness, everything is fascinating. From trees to shrubs and insects to animals, all the elements that make life on Earth beautiful, deserve protection. Srivilliputhur Sanctuary offers that haven to wildlife; and many memorable experiences to travellers.', 1),
(109, 1, 276, 2269, 'Right in the midst of a metropolitan urban settlement lies a serene strip of land, so relaxing and comforting. Living in its heart are a variety of species that are well protected and looked after. Guindy National Park is a wonder that Chennai has for the world.', 1),
(110, 1, 277, 2284, 'The lushness of wilderness that fills your heart with peace, the sheer joy of seeing amazing species of birds fly around everywhere, the pleasure of being one with Nature â the Vedanthangal Sanctuary is indeed a destination to relish the joys of life.', 1),
(111, 1, 278, 2302, 'Here they rest, in a pensive mood; sometimes looking as if lost in thoughts or meditation and at other times frolicking in the cool pool that is all theirs. The Crocodile Park in Tamil Nadu is indeed a place of great interest.', 1),
(112, 1, 279, 2318, 'Tucked away in the captivating wilderness, high up in the serene mountain ranges, is a fascinating destination that is home to many species of exotic fauna and flora. Nellai Wildlife Sanctuary is one of the finest of its kind in Tamil Nadu.', 1),
(113, 1, 280, 2348, 'Take a memorable drive from Madurai along the beautifully laid road dotted with trees on either side. The drive itself is a pleasure and what awaits you at Kumbakkarai falls is sheer joy. The scenic spot in the foothills of Kodaikkanal enjoys immense popularity among the famous tourist sites in Tamilnadu', 1),
(114, 1, 281, 2364, 'The beauty of Suruli waterfalls is such that it finds mention in the epic Silappathikaram. The place has an untamed appeal which offers an exhilarating experience for the tourists.', 1),
(115, 1, 282, 2385, 'If you love trekking, you will love the trek to one of the most spectacular waterfalls in Tamilnadu. Take a short drive from Kallakurichi in Villupuram and walk down the hill to reach this beautiful waterfall.', 1),
(116, 1, 283, 2401, 'When it comes to devotion and art, Tamil Nadu has its uniqueness and that is reflected in its Navaratri festival. Who would not want to visit a Tamil house during the Navaratri times to see the Kolu/Golu, a perfect blend of devotion and art!', 1),
(117, 1, 284, 2409, 'For a Tamilan, a Deepavali celebration starts with an early morning oil bath and ends by bursting crackers at night. Textile shops and sweet shops will be flooded by Diwali shopping customers. It is the peak business season for the firecracker industries in Sivakasi. ', 1),
(118, 1, 285, 2417, 'As per the Hindu traditions in Tamil Nadu, there is no better day than Vijayadashami for starting new ventures, projects, or learning the alphabets or any other art form. This is the day that comes after Mahanavami, where Puja is performed for Goddess Saraswathi in Tamil Nadu. In Tamil Nadu and Kerala, the Saraswathi  Puja is observed on the ninth day of the Navarathri festival. ', 1),
(119, 1, 286, 2425, 'A visit to Tamil Nadu is incomplete without witnessing the magnanimous and flamboyant carnival of the Madurai city - Chithirai festival. Despite the summer heat, people throng the streets of Madurai to see the union of their Lord Sundershwar and the Goddess, Meenakshi. A confluence of religion, art, entertainment and food barring all religious differences is what is Chithirai all about. ', 1),
(120, 1, 287, 2433, 'A journey of just 15 minutes from Ooty town centre will take you to the famed Pine Tree Forests of Ooty. These scenic woodlands, obscured in a fleeting veil of mist, offer a delightful experience to all travellers.', 1),
(121, 1, 288, 2449, 'An idyllic park to soak in the chilly weather that Ooty is known for, to sunbathe with the most picturesque sights to view, and to unwind.', 1),
(122, 1, 289, 2465, 'The Deer Park in Ooty is the perfect place to observe these docile creatures in their natural habitat. Located on the banks of the Ooty Lake is another beautiful park, a favourite among wildlife lovers.', 1),
(123, 1, 290, 2481, 'The Government Museum is a tourist attraction in Ooty where the tribal history and cultural background of the indigenous people are carefully documented, preserved and displayed.  This place is very likely to awaken the history buff in you, and you can educate as well as entertain yourself by exploring the history and culture of the land.', 1),
(124, 1, 291, 2497, 'Here, history blends seamlessly with the present; leaving a visitor astonished at the contrast of experiences. On one end, there is a bustling metropolitan city and on the other, a centre of culture, art and learning. Welcome to Chennai!', 1),
(125, 1, 293, 2519, 'Known as the Manchester of South India, Coimbatore is one of the most industrialized districts and a major textile, industrial, commercial, educational, information technology, healthcare and manufacturing hub of Tamil Nadu.\r\n\r\n', 1),
(126, 1, 294, 2535, 'An ancient city that takes you back in time; where you will stand wondering about the evolution of culture, traditions and civilization. Walk further and you will be amazed by how such a historic city has a bustling urban face too.\r\n', 1),
(127, 1, 295, 2551, 'Itâs a spectacular sight; how the vastness of the deep blue sky above mirrors the beauty of the sea below. A beach, so picturesque and quaint, nestles by the side being a source of fascination to the tens of thousands of tourists who visit it.', 1),
(128, 1, 296, 2567, NULL, 1),
(129, 1, 297, 2583, 'The sun, the sands and the water â the finest beach experiences that allure a traveller are right here in Dhanushkodi. The vastness and the deepness of the blue sea is a sight to behold; and the endless fascinations on the shore are all to be experienced.', 1),
(130, 1, 298, 2599, 'You think of visiting a waterfall and you end up infront of nine magnificent walls, magical, right. Coutrallam waterfalls is a beautiful destination for the perfect getaway.', 1),
(131, 1, 299, 2615, 'Rolling hills of Manjolai blanket the cascading Manimuthar falls. The scenic beauty of this place complete with green spread, hills, tea plantation, garden and a dam make Manimuthar falls one of the most loved tourist spots.', 1),
(132, 1, 300, 2631, 'This spectacular waterfall located amidst enchanting greenery is at once a most frequented pilgrim and tourism spot. This waterfall is 4km away from Papanasam town and 51 km drive from Tirunelveli.', 1),
(133, 1, 304, 2666, 'The Kapaleshwarar Temple in Mylapore, Chennai is dedicated to Lord Siva.', 1),
(134, 1, 308, 2689, 'Hogenakal translates as Smoky Rocks in Kannada. This waterfall situated on the border of Karnataka and in the district of Dharmapuri in Tamilnadu draws a good number of tourists for the splendid sights the place unravels.', 1),
(135, 1, 312, 2744, 'Explore the unspoiled beauty of nature at Kutladampatti waterfalls. The picturesque beauty of this place has made this one of the most loved tourist spots.', 1),
(136, 1, 313, 2760, 'Sri Ramkrishna Math in Chennai.', 1),
(137, 1, 314, 2764, 'Sri Ramkrishna Math in Chennai.', 1),
(138, 1, 315, 2768, 'Sri Ramkrishna Math in Chennai.', 1),
(139, 1, 316, 2772, 'For those who love natural springs in forests, Puliyancholai is the perfect choice. Located on the foothills of Kolli hills, the spot has an enchanting appeal making it an all time season favourite for tourists.', 1),
(140, 1, 317, 2788, 'Dreaming of a delightful vacation by a splendid seaside where you can watch sunrise and sunset in all its glory? Or simply walk around the place, mesmerised by the enchanting beauty and historic virtues it treats you with? Welcome to Kanyakumari.', 1),
(141, 1, 318, 2804, 'A visit to Vaidehi falls combines the joy of trekking along the forest and immersing yourself in the refreshing water. ', 1),
(142, 1, 319, 2819, 'A thick green cover of forest and plains with a carpet of tea plantation, add to it a double cascading waterfall, you get a picture of Catherine waterfall.', 1),
(143, 1, 320, 2835, 'A city of great traditions, flaunting its alluring old-age charm; at the same time surprising visitors with enchanting locations to spend their vacations. Kancheepuram combines its glorious past with its effervescent spirit to give you unique experiences of a lifetime.', 1),
(144, 1, 321, 2851, 'Here is where images from the past come together to paint the collage of a glorious city; a work of art in itself. that reflects the richness of culture and heritage that adorns this land. Thanjavur is a destination unlike any other.', 1),
(145, 1, 322, 2867, 'A fast-growing urban conglomerate, yet a land where you can slow down, enjoying the innate beauty of the destination. Here is a city where you get to enjoy it all â history, leisure, culture, cuisine and what not.', 1),
(146, 1, 323, 2883, 'A shimmering silver splash cutting across a thick foliage; there could be no better sight to come across on a road trip than this beautiful image. That\'s what Thalaiyar waterfall is all about and it is no surprise that it enjoys the distinction of being one of the most loved tourist spots in Tamil Nadu.', 1),
(147, 1, 324, 2899, 'If you are in the mood to explore an unspoilt destination, plan your trip to Monkey waterfalls. This beautiful waterfall is situated on the way to Pollachi. ', 1),
(148, 1, 325, 2915, 'There is more to this waterbody than being a leisurely spot to hangout on. Itâs a sacred place, filled with devotees round the year, seeking salvation and amusement. Agni Theertham shines brightly among the beaches of Tamil Nadu for more reasons than one.', 1),
(149, 1, 330, 2983, 'The golden sands, sight of the deep blue sea and the vastness it brings along, the cool breeze that calms you down â Muthu Nagar beach in Tamil Nadu is a location that any beach lover will instantly fall in love with.', 1),
(150, 1, 352, 3284, 'Sri Lakshmi Golden Temple at Vellore', 1),
(151, 1, 364, 3442, 'Nestled in the Shevaroys range of hills, Yercaud opens up a paradise of sights and things to explore. The origin of the place name sums up the main attractions; yeri means lake and forest means kaadu.', 1),
(152, 1, 370, 3527, 'Seek out the beauty of nature at its very best at Coonoor, the second largest hill station in the Nilgiri hills. For trekkers and tourists, the place serves up a lot to explore. Blanketed by the green cover of Nilgiri hills, it packs an array of attractions.\r\n', 1),
(153, 1, 375, 3588, 'Dr. A P J Abdul Kalam Memorial at Rameswaram.', 1),
(154, 1, 378, 3620, 'Marvel at the sky piercing mountains cloaked by clouds and carpeted by tea plantations at Meghamalai. A quiet hilly village where you get to experience the quaint nature and the simple village life. Tour the hamlet, make new friends, taste the local cuisine and savour the unique landscapes of Meghamalai. ', 1),
(155, 1, 382, 3678, 'Meenakshi Amman Temple in Madurai.', 1),
(156, 1, 384, 3696, 'Arunachaleshwar Temple at Tiruvannamalai.', 1),
(157, 1, 402, 3939, 'Here is where natural wonders and man-made masterpieces converge to provide a mind-blowing view. Itâs beautiful, inviting and majestic, all at the same time. The Kanyakumari Beach located in the Southern tip of India is for sure one for ages.', 1),
(158, 1, 404, 3969, 'Just a small drive from the heart of the city, but a blissful location that will win the hearts of every visitor. A beach buzzing with life, activities and the sheer pleasure of beach leisure. Thiruvanmiyoor beach is Chennaiâs gift for you.', 1),
(159, 1, 421, 4044, 'The sea is calm here. The sun shines above gleamingly and the coast reflects a shimmering aura that captivates and enthralls every single visitor. Covelong Beach is one such spectacular spot that is more than ideal for that perfect vacation.', 1),
(160, 1, 424, 4066, 'No matter how busy this beach gets, you still get to experience the tranquility that fills the air. Here is where a city comes together to celebrate every moment. Elliotâs Beach is a shore that reflects the richness of Chennaiâs soul.', 1),
(161, 1, 426, 4085, 'There are certain attractions that define a city in many unique ways; reflecting the essence, the character and the very soul of that destination. That is what Marina Beach is to Chennai â the cityâs heart that reflects everything that is best about the city.', 1),
(162, 1, 390, 4148, ' This beautiful, hilly hamlet of Valparai is the ultimate choice for those who wish to spend a quiet memorable time away from all the hustle. The lavish green spread, tea plantations and winding paths serve up a lot to explore. ', 1),
(163, 1, 357, 4149, 'Home to trekking and adventure activities, Yelagiri has captivating locale, lakes, temples, quaint hamlets which make it an ideal tourist destination', 1),
(164, 1, 443, 4152, 'Nilgiris is not just about Ooty and Coonoor, relax and unwind in the quaint air of Kotagiri hills. From trekking to rock climbing, discover plenty of options to make your trip memorable at Kotagiri.', 1),
(165, 1, 371, 4167, 'Winding through the slopes of Nilgiri Hills is the majestic river of Pykara. With its rolling waterfalls and pristine reservoir lake, Pykara reveals its true beauty during the monsoon and winter months. Located just 20 km away from Ooty town, Pykara is a perfect getaway destination for honeymooners, backpackers and families.', 1),
(166, 1, 368, 4169, 'Flirting with the clouds above the Nilgiris is Doddabetta, the highest peak in Tamil Nadu. A spectacular trail with an unparalleled vantage point of Ooty at the end of it makes Doddabetta a rewarding trekking experience and the perfect spot for a fun-filled day out with family as well.\r\n', 1),
(167, 1, 484, 4359, 'Grassy hills, forest, mountains, reservoirs and exotic flora and fauna- Anamalai hills is a paradise for nature lovers, travellers and trekkers.', 1),
(168, 1, 388, 4374, 'Gifted with pleasant weather throughout the year, Kolli hills is one of those round the season destinations in Tamil Nadu. Unique in landscape and attractions, it has a scenic beauty and has plenty to offer for the exploring travellers. ', 1),
(169, 1, 380, 4381, 'Madurai is synonymous with Sri Meenakshi Amman temple. A famous pilgrimage spot, the temple is renowned for its classic architectural style, stupendous structures and carvings. ', 1),
(170, 1, 489, 4440, 'Shirdi Sai Baba Temple at Mylapore in Chennai is a respected place of worship in Tamil Nadu. It is dedicated to 18th century Indian saint Sai Baba of Shirdi.', 1),
(171, 1, 493, 4499, 'Constructed in 1962, the temple was constructed in 1962 on a piece of land donated by Chithira Thirunal, the last Maharaja of Travancore. Constructed in the Kerala style, the temple caters to Chennaiâs Malayali community.', 1),
(172, 1, 497, 4554, 'According to a legend, the mosque got its name as in olden times thousand lamps were needed to illuminate the prayer hall. The mosque has a special significance for the Shia Muslims. It is dedicated to Imam Hossain, the grandson of Prophet Muhammad, who is respected among the Shia sect around the globe.   ', 1),
(173, 1, 501, 4614, 'The landscaped garden, ornamented parapets and colourful pathways give us a pleasant welcome. The main temple at the place is the Universal Temple. It is open to anyone irrespective of their caste, creed, gender or status in the society. ', 1),
(174, 1, 502, 4630, 'Also known as St Thomas Cathedral Basilica and National Shrine of Saint Thomas, San Thome Church is a Roman Catholic minor basilica at Santhome in Chennai. It was built over the tomb of Saint Thomas in the 16th century by Portuguese explorers.', 1),
(175, 1, 510, 4733, 'The Upper Bhavani Lake is one of the best-kept secrets of the Nilgiris. A pristine blue reservoir lake formed by a dam on the river Bhavani makes a perfect getaway spot for families and friends to enjoy a day out in nature.\r\n', 1),
(176, 1, 511, 4749, 'Framed by the mighty peaks of the Nilgiris and the rolling jade hillocks of tea plantations, is the Emerald Lake. Yet to be discovered by most travellers, Emerald Lake and its under-explored landscape that reminds you of a fairy-tale make a perfect location to spend a day enjoying the awe-inspiring views.\r\n', 1),
(177, 1, 512, 4765, 'Pamban beach which is located in Pamban island is an offbeat tourist destination in Rameswaram. The beach is one of the important fishing ports in Rameswaram and offers amazing views of the azure waters that stretch around the island.\r\n', 1),
(178, 1, 513, 4782, 'One of Indiaâs finest engineering marvels in India is the much-acclaimed Pamban rail bridge in Rameswaram that connects the island of Rameswaram to the mainland. The Pamban bridge holds historical significance as the first-ever bridge built across the sea in India.\r\n', 1),
(179, 1, 372, 4798, 'Ramanathaswamy temple is a popular place of worship and prominent tourist attraction in Rameshwaram. The shrine is dedicated to Lord Shiva and is one of the twelve jyotirlinga temples in India.\r\n', 1),
(180, 1, 514, 4801, 'Rameshwaram is known for its pilgrimage sites, and there are many mythological stories tied to the various religious destinations in the district. One such important pilgrim destination is the Panchamukhi Hanuman temple which is situated just 2 km from Sri Ramanathaswamy temple in Rameswaram.\r\n', 1),
(181, 1, 515, 4817, 'Nestled atop a hill and surrounded by dense forest, Pazhamudhircholai attracts devouts in good numbers. It is one among the six abodes of Lord Muruga; Thiruparankundram Subramanya Swamy Temple, Palani Dandayudhapani Swami Temple, Swamimalai Swaminatha Swami Temple, Tiruchendur Senthil Andavar Temple and Tiruttani Subramanya Swamy Temple being the other abodes.\r\n\r\n', 1),
(182, 1, 301, 4833, 'One of the imposing religious sites of Chennai city is the noted Kapaleeswarar Temple that is majestically set in the Mylapore region of Chennai. It is said the Shiva Lingam in the temple is Swayambulingam, which means it is self-manifested.', 1),
(183, 1, 516, 4836, 'Itâs a shore that witnessed several historic moments that defined the course of South India. The coastline evolved with time and is today one of the most visited tourism destinations in Tamil Nadu. The Mahabalipuram is a spot worth every hype.\r\n', 1),
(184, 1, 517, 4853, 'A shore that brims with beauty, history and legends; virtues that have lasted generations and will continue to be so for all the times to come. Ariyaman Beach in Rameswaram is an idyllic spot to spend a splendid vacation full of great experiences.\r\n', 1),
(185, 1, 518, 4870, 'A shore with many lores that have been told across centuries; fascinating, enigmatic and poetic. Olaikuda beach, one of the finest beaches in the quaint town of Rameswaram is also a tourism hotspot in Tamil Nadu for more than one.\r\n', 1),
(186, 1, 519, 4887, 'Sun-kissed sands, serene waters, a resplendent shore brimming with natural beauty â here is your picture-perfect vacation spot that you would love to visit over and over again. Sangumal Beach, rich in a variety of amazing experiences is indeed a must-visit destination in Tamil Nadu.\r\n', 1);
