(210, 1, 367, 3485, '<p>Hidden away from the commotions of urban jungles is the Avalanche Lake, a naturally formed crystal blue freshwater body. Nestled between the green slopes of the Nilgiris, the Avalanche Lake is a picture-perfect location set just over 20 km away from Ooty town. The lake, with its refreshing blue waters and soothing greenery of the surrounding woods, is a treat for anyone in search of a getaway destination to escape the fatigue of mundane life. The lake has some of the best views of the Nilgiris, overlooking the undulating hills draped in perfectly aligned tea plants and the opulent greenery of the woods, all in the background of a picturesque lake always veiled in a white fog. The Avalanche Lake and its surroundings are a pristine tract of the Western Ghats, immaculately maintained with the help of local tribes. Avalanche Lake will be an enthralling experience for anyone who wants a getaway spot to escape into the raw beauty of nature and be lost and undisturbed in its serenity.</p>\r\n<p>Avalanche Lakeshore is one of the best camping spots in Ooty. Set camp on the shores and wake up to the enchanting view of the sun rising over the mist-clad mountains. The woods around the lake have winding trails that lead you to some of the best hidden treasures in Ooty. The lake is open for fishing after the monsoons. The nearby trout hatchery has all the basic gear and essentials you need to spend your afternoons relaxing while engaging in some trout fishing in the lake. Pack your bags and head to the Avalanche Lake to escape the screaming madness of city life and enjoy the tranquillity and pristine beauty of nature.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(211, 1, 368, 3499, '<p>Rising above the misty green valleys of Ooty with its 2,637 meters of height, Doddabetta stands up to its name which translates to &ldquo;big mountain.&rdquo; Perfectly placed between Eastern and Western Ghats the Doddabetta peak is the perfect destination to head to cherish the beauty of the landscape of Nilgiris in its entirety. Offering a bird&rsquo;s eye view of Ooty framed by the misty green hills of Nilgiris, Doddabetta is a challenging yet rewarding climb of almost 3 kms. A winding trail winding through grassy slopes is disturbed only by the foggy mountain breeze and will take you to a awe-inspiring view of the Ooty in the backdrop of rolling Nilgiri hills.</p>\r\n<p>Countless rugged and rustic trails winding through hillocks and countryside for around 10 kms from the Ooty town will take you to the foot of Doddabetta where you will be welcomed by a steep climb. The seemingly challenging trail amidst green slopes of the peak will prove effortless as it gets you closer to the clouds. At the summit a telescope house awaits trekkers to bless them with a 360-degree panoramic view of the blue misty mountains of Nilgiris. One can be lost in the stunning views of the opulent greenery of the Bandipur National Park and green plains of Coimbatore and Mysore spanning the horizon. For a refreshing hot cup of tea atop the peak, one can head to the Doddabetta Tea Factory where an enthralling taste and aroma of freshly grown tea awaits. Any true connoisseurs of tea must add the annual Tea and Tourism Festival conducted at the tea factory to their travel itinerary. With its wild charm and jaw-dropping views Doddabetta and its atmosphere rich in aroma awaits any trekker weary of the noises and fatigue of the mundane life.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(212, 1, 369, 3513, '<p>A trip along the winding roads of the Ooty-Coonoor route will take you to the jaw-dropping views of one of the largest valleys in the world. Extending from the plains of Coimbatore all the way to the Mysore Plateau, Ketty Valley is an overwhelming expanse of greenery and picturesque hamlets. Hidden away amongst the heights of the Nilgiris in Ooty, Ketty Valley offers an astonishing panorama of the unending greenery guarded by the Western Ghats. The enchanting views of the valley and its pristine ambiance are a much sought-after solace by countless weary minds every year. Ketty Valley blesses travellers with a breath-taking view and an opportunity to explore its countless serene hamlets. Ketty Valley is a popular destination amongst travellers in search of inner peace and the solace of nature. Blessed with surreal vistas of the rolling blue hills of Nilgiris and the unending greenery, Ketty Valley is a perfect weekend getaway destination. With its opulence of greenery and peaks veiled in fog, Ketty Velley is nothing short of a piece of heaven dropped from the skies.</p>\r\n<p>Experiencing a sunrise and a sunset over Ketty Valley should be on the itinerary of anyone visiting the Queen of Hill Stations. There is no better place to take a break from the head-spinning rush of everyday life and take a moment to be one with nature. Let the roaming winds of the valley carry away the burdens of your mind as you enjoy the endless canvas painted in crimson and amber by the sun&rsquo;s slanting rays. With its gushing waterfalls, ever-present white fog and a bird&rsquo;s eye view of the expanses of the valley, Ketty Valley is a photographer&rsquo;s paradise offering a perfect backdrop to capture your happy moments with your friends and family. Pack your bags and head to Ketty Valley to listen to the songs the winds of the valley will sing for you.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(213, 1, 370, 3528, '<p>With its spellbinding set of viewpoints, sprawling hills , waterfalls and luxuriant greenery, Coonoor is your perfect getaway spot. Take a stroll along the tea plantations clouded in mist. Spend time in the valleys and near the waterfalls. Click some amazing pictures. Gear up for a memorable trekking experience. Cut your way through the hills and make it to the top to some of the most spectacular views. Drop by the town and discover artefacts and souvenirs. If you love birds, head to Sim\'s park, considered as one of the top attractions of Coonoor hills. Surprise yourself with the sight of bulbuls, babblers and robins. Listen carefully to the sounds of birds and if lucky, spot them just like that.</p>\r\n<p>Named after J D Sim, a former secretary to the Government, Sim\'s park houses unique species of plants and shrubs as well. Plan your trip to witness the annual fruits and vegetable show held here. Notable landmarks include the Lamb\'s rock, Dolphin\'s nose, Catherine falls, law\'s&nbsp; falls and droog fort. Trek your way to the top of Lamb\'s rock, it would tire you a bit, but the spectacular view is worth the effort. If you are fit, go for it. Enjoy the beauty of sunrise and sunset at the Dolphin\'s nose viewpoint. Get the best view of Catherine Falls from here. Experience local shopping at Coonoor and walk home with some exquisite products. The train ride from Coonoor to Ooty is something you don\'t want to miss. Make sure you leave ample time to explore the best of Coonoor.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(214, 1, 371, 3543, '<p>Originating from the heights of Mukurthi Hills, Pykara river cuts through the misty heights of Nilgiris and navigates itself to the rolling green hills and valleys, creating some of the most picturesque views in Ooty. Revered by the locals as a sacred river, the untouched landscapes carved by the Pykara offers an enchanting experience to a soul in search of tranquillity. As it traverses through the steep slopes, Pykara transforms itself into graceful waterfalls. The atmosphere enriched with sweet lullaby of Pykara falls and chilly mist rolling on and off from the river makes it an ideal spot for trekking and camping. Removed from the fatigue and noises of the urban life, Pykara waterfalls and its surrounding woods are calling you to enjoy a refreshing weekend getaway.</p>\r\n<p>As it enters the gentler slopes of Nilgiris, Pykara paints picturesque landscapes against the backdrop of the rolling green hills and valleys. These grass hills are home to the Todas &ndash; a Dravidian ethnic group living in the Nilgiris. Pykara, in the backdrop of the Toda hamlet and their traditional dwellings offers to the trekker a pristine and idyllic scenery.</p>\r\n<p>Just 2 km from the waterfalls the rolling waters of the Pykara turns into a serene blue reservoir lake. The view of the lapping waters of the Pykara Lake bordered by tall pine trees against the background of green misty hills of Nilgiris is an enthralling view to behold. The impeccable views and the everlasting misty breeze from the lake fills the atmosphere with romance, making it a popular honeymoon destination. The lake has best boating facilities in Ooty with various options made available through the boathouse run by Tamil Nadu Tourism Development Corporation. With its serene atmosphere, enticing views and boating facilities, Pykara Lake is the perfect destination in Ooty to spend a day with your family.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(215, 1, 372, 3557, '<p>Ramanathaswamy temple is known for its imposing structure, majestic towers, intricate sculptural&nbsp; works and corridors, making it an architectural marvel. The main deity worshipped in the temple is in the form of lingam. There is also an idol of Nandi, which is a massive statue, about 17.5 feet tall. Other deities worshipped here include Goddess Vishalakshi, Parvathavardhini, Lord Vinayaka and Lord Subrahmanya, Utsava idol, Sayanagriha and Perumal.</p>\r\n<p>The legend behind the temple is associated with Lord Rama from the Indian epic Ramayana. It is believed that Lord Rama, after defeating the demon king Ravana, wanted to worship Lord Shiva as part of atonement. He asks Hanuman to bring him a Linga from Kashi. When Hanuman delayed his return, Goddess Sita made a Shivalinga using sand so that Rama could offer his prayers. It is believed that the self-same Shiva Linga, known as Ramalingam, is now worshipped at the Ramanathaswamy temple. The lingam brought by Hanuman from Kailash is called Vishwalingam.</p>\r\n<p>There are 22 Theerthams (holy water bodies) inside the temple where devotees bathe to atone for their sins.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(216, 1, 374, 3574, '<p>Spread over 2.11 acres of land, the Abdul Kalam Memorial was inaugurated by Prime Minister Narendra Modi in 2017. The Defence Research and Development Organization (DRDO) initiated the construction of the memorial to pay tribute to India&rsquo;s missile man. Construction of the memorial began on the burial ground where Dr Kalam was laid to rest in 2015.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The memorial has been structured through careful planning, taking into consideration Dr Kalam&rsquo;s interests and likes. The entrance of the main gate looks similar to the India Gate, which also has a touch of the Chettinad style resembling the door of Brihadeeswarar Temple in Thanjavur. The main dome is a replica of the Rashtrapathi Bhavan. There is also a bronze statue of Dr Kalam playing the veena.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The memorial consists of four halls that reflect various facets of Dr Kalam&rsquo;s life, including the Pokhran atomic test. There are replicas of rockets, missiles and paintings all of which highlight his association with the Defence Research and Development Organization (DRDO) and Indian Space Research Organization (ISRO).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The garden outside the memorial resembles a Mughal Garden and is decorated with plants brought from Bangalore, Andhra Pradesh and Telengana. There are also other hand picked blossoms that accord with Dr Kalam&rsquo;s taste.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This exemplary memorial and the well-thought-out efforts behind each segment was completed only in 25 days&rsquo; time.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The second phase of the memorial will incorporate a library, a planetarium and an auditorium.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(217, 1, 376, 3592, '<p>It&rsquo;s a sight to behold &ndash; the majesty of the Thiruvalluvar Statue that can be seen from a long distance. It stands tall at 41 metres, with the deep blue sky and resplendent sea in the backdrop. Located on a rock, right next to the Vivekananda Rock Memorial in Kanyakumari, the breathtaking statue of Thiruvalluvar was created by the Indian sculptor V. Ganapathi Sthapathi and was dedicated to the people of Tamil Nadu on January 1, 2000 by the then Chief Minister of Tamil Nadu M. Karunanidhi.</p>\r\n<p>Thiruvalluvar was a celebrated Tamil poet and scholar and is best known as the author of &lsquo;Tirukkural&rsquo;, a collection of couplets on matters like ethics, politics, economics and love. Tirukkural is considered one of the greatest works in Tamil literature. The total height of the statue and the pedestal combined is 133 feet (41 metres). It denotes the 133 chapters of the Tirukkural. The sculpture of Thiruvalluvar is 95 feet (29 metres) and it stands on a 38 feet (12 metres) pedestal that represents the 38 chapters of virtue, the first of three books of the Kural text. The second and third books &ndash; wealth and love respectively &ndash; are represented by the statue itself. The statue weighs 7000 tonnes in total. The statue is built as per Indian architectural styles, and is hollow inside. However, tourists are allowed to climb only up to the foot of the statue.</p>\r\n<p>Along with the Vivekananda Rock Memorial, the statue attracts millions of tourists annually and is one of the must-visit spots in your trip to Tamil Nadu.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
