(239, 1, 400, 3911, '<p>The serene Sanjeevi hills has many mentions in the Indian epic Ramayana and is considered a sacred mountain among Hindus. As per the myths, the lofty Sanjeevi hills was once part of the Dronagiri range of the Himalayas. In Ramayana, Lord Lakshman was injured badly during the war against the demon king Ravana. Lord Hanuman was then instructed by Lord Rama to bring the Sanjeevi mountain, which was replete with medicinal herbs, to cure Lakshman&rsquo;s illness. It is thus considered a holy mountain that contains many medicinal herbs across its landscape.</p>\r\n<p>Besides the religious significance, the Sanjeevi hills is also characterised by its dense forests, lush vegetation and peaceful environment.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
