(245, 1, 421, 4045, '<p>Not all beaches are the same. Some stand out for their sheer, pristine serenity that makes them a dream destination by all means. Covelong Beach is of beyond doubt one such special locale that attracts tourists from all parts of the world. The golden sands, the exciting tides, the sheer ambiance that calls for celebration &ndash; Covelong Beach has it all for that ideal time out on the shore. The beach provides views and experiences that are truly memorable.&nbsp;<br /><br />This charming beach is located in the fishing village of Covelong, located 40 km away from Chennai. The port town of Covelong was established by the Nawab of Carnatic. The original name of this destination is &lsquo;Kovalam&rsquo; and the beach is often referred to as the Kovalam beach. The port is visible from the beach and offers the visitors a grand and stunning view. Located in the Coromandel coast along the Bay of Bengal, the Covelong Beach is located on the way to Mahabalipuram, making it a perfect stopover destination for visitors. One of the most distinctive features of this beach is that it is separated from the mainland of India, serving as a subject of great fascination. The beach is more than a serene location to relax and enjoy the sea, but also a centre for adventures such as windsurfing.&nbsp;<br /><br />There are several other attractions of tourist interest located near to the Covelong beach. All these make the beach and the village that is famous for fishing activities, a must-visit destination on your visit to Tamil Nadu.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(246, 1, 424, 4067, '<p>Be it for a leisurely stroll, or to spend a beautiful evening in the company of family or friends, here is a beach that provides the ideal ambiance for it. Edward Elliot&rsquo;s Beach or Elliot&rsquo;s beach as it is popularly known is one of Chennai&rsquo;s favourite hangout spots. One of the cleanest and most pristine beaches in South India, the Elliot&rsquo;s beach is located in Besant Nagar, one of the bustling neighbourhoods of Chennai. For this reason, the beach is also often referred to as the Besant Nagar Beach.</p>\r\n<p>No trip to Chennai is considered complete without a visit to the Elliot&rsquo;s Beach. Such is the charm these sands and waves exude. The beach is named after Edward Francis Elliot, a chief magistrate and superintendent of police from the British days in the region. One of the major landmarks of the beach is the Karl Schmidt Memorial, erected in the memory of a Dutch Sailor who sacrificed his life while trying to save a girl from drowning. The Elliot&rsquo;s Beach is the end-point of the Marina Beach Shore and is one of the most idyllic spots in the city. Though located close to the city centre, this beach isn&rsquo;t overcrowded on most days; a factor that lets you enjoy the beauty of the deep blue sea and the splendid sands. There are many activities that you can enjoy on the shore including horse riding and checking out the delicacies around.</p>\r\n<p>Also, the beach is located pretty close to various tourist attractions that Chennai has in store.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(247, 1, 426, 4086, '<p>It&rsquo;s a landmark that Chennai has been proudly showcasing before the world &ndash; the Marina Beach. A splendidly serene strip of coast along the Bay of Bengal, the Marina Beach is considered to be one of the finest beaches in India. No wonder the spot attracts thousands of visitors everyday from all parts of the world. The first choice of local people when it comes to spending a beautiful evening, Marina Beach is one of the largest urban beaches in the world.</p>\r\n<p>Stretching across 13 kms from Fort St. George to the northern part of Besant Nagar, this beach was nothing but a stretch of mud before the construction of the Madras Port. The same was modified to form a promenade and was named the Madras Marina by the British. During the Indian freedom struggle, the Marina Beach was a centre for social gatherings and public events. With the passage of time, Marina Beach transformed itself into a locale of leisure and entertainment. It is estimated that over 30,000 people visit the beach everyday, making the entire 13 km stretch buzzing with life.</p>\r\n<p>The views of the sea, the sand and the sunrise are ones to enjoy from Marina Beach. Though a popular beach destination, Marina beach isn&rsquo;t considered safe to swim or host water sports due to the turbulent undercurrent. However, taking a stroll on the beach itself is an experience like few others. A 50 m high lighthouse on the beach offers a spectacular view of the city and surroundings.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(248, 1, 443, 4153, '<p style=\"text-align: left;\">One has to thank the two former civil servants of the Madras Government who had a chance discovery of this beautiful place while they were pursuing outlaws. They found the chilly climate similar to that of Europe. Blessed with green meadows,lavish spread of plantations, Kotagiri is the ideal spot to spend some leisurely time. Take a walk along the plantations, drop in at the tea factories for a tea tasting session and pack home some of the best tea powder you will come across.&nbsp;<br /><br />Head to Catherine falls, Elk falls,&nbsp; Doddabetta range and Rangaswami pillar in and around the place. Take in the magnificent view of the mist-cloaked hills and valleys. The fact that it is less explored makes it a place of unspoilt beauty. For the trekkers, take the famous trails ; St. Catherine Falls trail, the Kotagiri&ndash;Kodanad trail and the Kotagiri&ndash;Longwood Shola trail. Situated at a height of 1793 metres above sea level, Kotagiri is famed for the multiple options it offers for trekking expeditions. Even for others, it has options to spend quiet, relaxing time here and the well connected network of roads makes it easily accessible.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
