(260, 1, 489, 4441, '<p>Shirdi Sai Baba Temple at Mylapore in Chennai is a popular place of worship in Tamil Nadu. It is dedicated to the 18th century Indian saint Sai Baba of Shirdi.</p>\r\n<p>The temple acts as the headquarters of All India Sai Samaj whose founder Narasimha Swamiji started the temple as well. One striking feature of&nbsp; the temple is that people of any religious background can visit it. In fact, the temple has a fixed schedule to read the Quran and the Bible. It is a peaceful retreat not only for the followers of the saint but also for believers of other faiths.</p>\r\n<p>The architecture of the temple is striking. The white marble along with a golden arch on the wall of the shrine lifts the ambience of the place to a spiritual plane. Made of white marble, the idol of Sai Baba rests on a throne of sparkling silver. The fire burning inside the temple is said to be part of the original flame that was lit by Sai Baba at Shirdi. The place houses the shrines of Lord Rama and Lord Krishna as well. Thursdays are busy days at the temple as there are special prayers and feast (annadhanam).&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Navarathri and Guru Purnima are the main festival days at the temple.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
