(293, 1, 374, 3579, NULL, 'Dr. A P J Abdul Kalam Memorial | Rameswaram | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Dr. A P J Abdul Kalam Memorial, Rameswaram, places to visit in rameswaram, kalam house, kalam memorial, things to do in rameswaram, dhanuskodi, tamil nadu tourism, ', 'Avul Pakir Jainulabdeen Abdul Kalam, better known as Dr. A. P. J. Abdul Kalam was the 11th president of India. Kalam was born and brought up in Rameswaram and became a scientist and worked for DRDO and ISRO. After his sudden demise at Shillong on 27th July 2015, he was laid to rest at Pei Karumbu, Rameswaram on 30th July 2015. A memorial has been built at the burial site.', 'dr-apj-abdul-kalam-memorial', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(294, 1, 376, 3597, NULL, 'Thiruvalluvar Statue | Kanyakumari | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Thiruvalluvar Statue, Kanyakumari, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'The gigantic statue of Tamil Poet Thiruvalluvar, standing atop an island few metres into the sea is one of the major tourist attractions of Kanyakumari in Tamil Nadu. Standing tall at 133 feet, the statue of Thiruvalluvar was opened to the public in 2000. The statue stands on a three-tier pedestal, known as the Atharapeedam which is further surrounded by a 38 feet Alankara Peedam.', 'thiruvalluvar-statue ', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(295, 1, 377, 3611, NULL, 'Kanyakumari Beach | Pilgrim Centre | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Kanyakumari Beach, Pilgrim Centre, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'The southernmost coast of the Indian peninsula, Kanyakumari Beach is one of the pristine tourist attractions in South India. Located at the confluence of Arabian Sea, Indian Ocean, and the Bay of Bengal, this beach is famous for its unique ocean sunrise, sunset and moonrise. ', 'kanyakumari-beach', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(296, 1, 378, 3626, NULL, 'Meghamalai | Destinations | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Meghamalai', 'Untouched by the spate of buildings, Meghamalai dabbles in a special charm. The ever pleasant weather, the quiet air and the spectacular sights make this place one of the most favored destinations. Notable landmarks here include the wildlife sanctuary, Meghamalai waterfalls, Suruli waterfalls, dams, Maharaja Mettu view point, tea, cardamom plantations and Vellimalai.', 'meghamalai', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(297, 1, 379, 3640, NULL, 'Vivekananda Rock Memorial | Kanyakumari | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Vivekananda Rock Memorial, Tamil Nadu tourism', 'Vivekananda Rock Memorial is a monument and popular tourist attraction in Kanyakumari, India\'s southernmost tip,  built to commemorate the great religious reformer Swami Vivekananda. Opened to the public in 1970, the rock memorial is a major tourist attraction in Kanyakumari. ', 'vivekananda-rock-memorial', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(298, 1, 380, 3655, NULL, 'Madurai Meenakshi Amman Temple | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Madurai Meenakshi Amman Temple, Tamil Nadu Tourism, madurai meenakshi, temples in madurai, most famous temple in tamil nadu, pilgrim tourism, pilgrim centres in tamil nadu,  Meenakshi Sundareshwarar Temple, Arulmigu Meenakshi Amman Temple', 'Arulmigu Meenakshi Amman Temple, also known as Meenakshi Sundareshwarar Temple, is a historic Hindu temple located on the southern bank of the Vaigai River in the temple city of Madurai, Tamil Nadu, India. It is dedicated to the goddess Meenakshi, a form of Parvati, and her consort, Sundareshwarar, a form of Shiva.', 'meenakshi-amman-temple', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(299, 1, 381, 3669, NULL, 'Aayiram Kaal Mandapam | Madurai Meenakshi Amman Temple | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Aayiram Kaal Mandapam, Madurai Meenakshi Amman Temple, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Aayiram Kaal Mandapam, the Thousand-Pillared Hall, located inside Meenakshi Temple houses nearly 1000 pillars that are intricately carved upholding exquisite Dravidian architecture. The hall was built by Ariyanatha Mudaliar in 1569 and blends engineering skill and artistic vision. Maintained by the Archaeological Survey of India (ASI), the monument puts every visitor in awe of its beauty.', 'aayiram-kaal-mandapam', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(300, 1, 383, 3687, NULL, 'Arunachaleshwar Temple | Thiruvannamalai | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Arunachaleshwar Temple, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Arunachaleshwar Temple, also called Annamalaiyar Temple, is a Hindu temple dedicated to the deity Shiva, located at the base of Arunachala hill in the town of Thiruvannamalai in Tamil Nadu, India. The temple complex covers 10 hectares, and is one of the largest in India. It houses four gateway towers known as gopurams.', 'arunachaleshwar-temple', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
