(322, 1, 421, 4050, NULL, 'Covelong Beach | Destinations | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Covelong Beach, chennai beaches, beaches in tamil nadu, tamil nadu tourism, chennai tourism, tourist destinations in chennai, marina beach, covelong fishing village, ', 'The port town of Covelong was established by the Nawab of Carnatic. The original name of this destination is âKovalamâ and the beach is often referred to as the Kovalam beach. The port is visible from the beach and offers the visitors a grand and stunning view. ', 'covelong-beach', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(323, 1, 424, 4072, NULL, 'Elliotâs Beach | Destinations | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Elliotâs Beach, Besant Nagar beach, besant nagar, chennai, beaches in chennai, places to visit in chennai, chennai tourism, things to do in chennai, tamil nadu tourism, ', 'No trip to Chennai is considered complete without a visit to the Elliotâs Beach. Such is the charm these sands and waves exude. The beach is named after Edward Francis Elliot, a chief magistrate and superintendent of police from the British days in the region.', 'elliotâs-beach', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(324, 1, 426, 4091, NULL, 'Marina Beach | Destinations | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Marina Beach, chennai most famous beach, chennai tourism, beaches in tamil nadu, tamil nadu tourism, visit chennai, chennai tourist places, beaches in chennai, ', 'Stretching across 13 kms from Fort St. George to the northern part of Besant Nagar, Marina beach was nothing but a stretch of mud before the construction of the Madras Port. The same was modified to form a promenade and was named the Madras Marina by the British.', 'marina-beach', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(325, 1, 443, 4158, NULL, 'Kotagiri | Hill Stations | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Kotagiri, hill stations in tamil nadu, hills, the nilgiris, nilgiri hills, hill stations in nilgiris, Catherine falls, Elk falls,  Doddabetta range, Rangaswami pillar, ooty, coonoor,  tamil nadu tourism, ', 'Blessed with green meadows,lavish spread of plantations, Kotagiri is the ideal spot to spend some leisurely time. Take a walk along the plantations, drop in at the tea factories for a tea tasting session and pack home some of the best tea powder you will come across. Head to Catherine falls, Elk falls,  Doddabetta range and Rangaswami pillar in and around the place.', 'kotagiri', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
