(332, 1, 484, 4365, NULL, 'Anamalai | Hill Stations | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Anamalai, hill stations in tamil nadu, tamil nadu tourism, tourist destinations in tamil nadu, anamalai hills, anamalai tiger reserve, anamalai hill station, elephant hills, ', 'Spread over 600 sq.miles of forest, Anamalai houses a wide variety of animals and some rare collections of birds are also spotted here. The place is also dotted with tea and coffee plantations and the spread of teak forests. Visit the Indira Gandhi wildlife sanctuary and spot civet cats, tigers, panthers, wild boars, spotted deer and many more surprises. ', 'anamalai', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(333, 1, 485, 4389, NULL, 'Pulicat Lake | Bird Watching in Tamil Nadu | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Pulicat Lake, Bird Watching in Tamil Nadu, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Pulicat Lake is a narrow water lagoon connecting Pulicat city in Tiruvallur District of Tamil Nadu. It is situated almost 60 km north of Chennai city particularly on the seaward side of Sri Harikota island blockade that segregates Pulicat Lake from the Bay of Bengal. ', 'pulicat-lake', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(334, 1, 486, 4403, NULL, 'Swaminatha Swamy Temple | Swami Malai | Thanjavur | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Swaminatha Swamy Temple, Swami Malai, Thanjavur,Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Swaminatha Swamy Temple is a Hindu temple dedicated to god Murugan. It is located in Swamimalai, 5 km from Kumbakonam, on the banks of a tributary of river Kaveri in Thanjavur District, 250 km from Chennai, the capital of Tamil Nadu, India. Dedicated to Lord Murugan, the temple is almost thousand years\' old and continues to attract as many devotees. ', 'swami-malai-thanjavur', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(335, 1, 487, 4417, NULL, 'Saraswathi Mahal Library | Place of Interest | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Saraswathi Mahal Library, Place of Interest, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Saraswathi Mahal Library, also called Thanjavur Maharaja Serfoji\'s Saraswathi Mahal Library is a library located in Thanjavur, Tamil Nadu, India.', 'saraswathi-mahal-library', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(336, 1, 488, 4431, NULL, 'The Punnainallur Mariamman Temple | Thanjavur | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'The Punnainallur Mariamman Temple, Thanjavur, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'The Punnainallur Mariamman Temple is a Hindu temple located at Thanjavur in the state of Tamil Nadu, India. The temple of goddess Mariamman is located in the outskirts of Thanjavur. The temple is maintained and administered by the Hindu Religious and Charitable Endowments Department of the Government of Tamil Nadu. ', 'punnainallur-mariamman-temple', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(337, 1, 489, 4446, NULL, 'Shirdi Sai Baba Temple | Pilgrim Centres | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Shirdi Sai Baba Temple, temples in tamil nadu, chennai temples, pilgrim centres, pilgrim touism, tamil nadu tourism\r\n\r\n', 'Shirdi Sai Baba Temple at Mylapore in Chennai is a respected place of worship in Tamil Nadu. It is dedicated to 18th century Indian saint Sai Baba of Shirdi.', 'shirdi-sai-baba-temple', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(338, 1, 490, 4462, NULL, 'Alamparai Fort | Kancheepuram | Tamil Nadu', 'Alamparai Fort, Kancheepuram, Tamil Nadu, Mamallapuram', 'The ruins of Alamparai Fort (also called Alampara) lie near Kadappakkam, a village 50 km from Mamallapuram in Kancheepuram District in Tamil Nadu. Constructed in the late 17th century during the Mughal era, the Alamparai Fort once had a 100-metre long dockyard stretching into the sea, from which zari cloth, salt, and ghee were exported. ', 'alamparai fort', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(339, 1, 491, 4475, NULL, 'Sri Subramaniya Swami Temple | Kancheepuram | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Sri Subramaniya Swami Temple, kancheepuram, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Sri Subramaniya Swami Temple is located at Kancheepuram District in Tamil Nadu. The presiding deity here are the three major Hindu Gods-Lord Shiva with his consort Shakti is seen sitting on his left with their son Subramaniya sitting in between them. A revered place of worship, this temple is a must visit while on a tour of Kanchipuram.', 'sri-subramaniya-swami-temple', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(340, 1, 492, 4490, NULL, 'Kottai Mariamman Temple | Salem | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Kottai Mariamman Temple, Salem,  Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'One of the oldest pilgrimage spots in Salem, the Kottai Mariamman Temple is located near the banks of the River Tirumanimuthar in Salem District in Tamil Nadu. The presiding deity of the temple happens to be Kottai Mariamman, a form of Shakti. The temple is probably the only shrine in Tamil Nadu where devotees need to bow down to pay homage to the Goddess.', 'kottai-mariamman-temple', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(341, 1, 493, 4503, NULL, 'Anantha Padmanabha Swamy Temple | Pilgrim Centres | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Anantha Padmanabha Swamy Temple\r\n', 'Anantha Padmanabha Swamy Temple at Adyar in Chennai is named after the renowned Sree Padmanabhaswamy Temple in Thiruvananthapuram. The main deity is Lord Vishnu who is depicted reclining on a mythological five-headed serpent as in the Sree Padmanabhaswamy Temple in Thiruvananthapuram. The sight is really captivating and we cannot stop admiring the beauty of the deity.', 'anantha-padmanabha-swamy-temple', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(342, 1, 494, 4517, NULL, '1008 Lingam Temple | Salem | Tamil Nadu Tourism', '1008 Lingam Temple', 'A prominent religious shrine in Salem, the 1008 Lingam Temple situated atop a small mountain in the suburbs of Salem District in Tamil Nadu. The temple is dedicated to Lord Shiva. There are 1008 Shiva Lingams inside the shrine along with a statue of Nandi the Bull positioned right the centre of the temple referred to as the moolsthanam.', '1008-lingam-temple', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(343, 1, 495, 4531, NULL, 'The Mettur Dam | Salem District | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'The Mettur Dam, Salem District, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'The Mettur Dam at Salem District is the largest dam in the state of Tamil Nadu. Constructed along the Kaveri River, the dam was built in 1934 to provide irrigation facilities to Salem and its neighbouring regions.', 'the-mettur-dam', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(344, 1, 496, 4545, NULL, 'Sankagiri Fort | Salem District | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Sankagiri Fort, Salem District, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Sankagiri Fort in Salem District is a historical fort maintained by the Archaeological Survey of India. It is located 22 km from the city of Erode and 38 km from Salem. Sankari or Sankagiri is the town located around this place.', 'sankagiri-fort', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(345, 1, 497, 4560, NULL, 'Thousand Lights Mosque | pilgrim Centres | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Thousand Lights Mosque\r\n', 'Standing at the junction of Mount Road and Peters Road in the Royapettah neighbourhood, Thousand Lights Mosque at Chennai is one of the most revered mosques in the city. The cream-coloured, multi-domed mosque with walls bearing sayings from the Holy Quran is an important gathering place for daily prayers and other festive occasions.', 'thousand-lights-mosque', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(346, 1, 498, 4578, NULL, 'Samanar Hills | Madurai District | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Samanar Hills, madurai District, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Samanar Hills, also known as Samanar Malai or Amanarmalai or Melmalai, is a rocky stretch of hills located near Keelakuyilkudi village, 10 km west of Madurai city, Tamil Nadu, India. They stretch eastâwest over 3 km towards Muthupatti village. These rocky hillocks are home to many Jain and Hindu monuments. The hill has been declared as a protected monument by the Archaeological Survey of India.', 'samanar-hills', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(347, 1, 499, 4591, NULL, 'Arjunaâs Penance | Mahabalipuram | World Heritage Site | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Arjunaâs Penance, Mahabalipuram, World Heritage Site, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Arjunaâs Penance is one of the top heritage sites at Mahabalipuram in Chengalpet District in Tamil Nadu. It is the Worldâs largest bas relief Measuring 96 ft by 43 ft. The giant open-air rock relief carved on two monolithic rock boulders is one of the Group of Monuments at Mamallapuram that were designated as a UNESCO World Heritage Site since 1984.', 'arjunas-penance', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(348, 1, 500, 4605, NULL, 'Krishna\'s Butterball | Mahabalipuram | World Heritage Site | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Krishna\'s Butterball, Mahabalipuram, World Heritage Site, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Krishna\'s Butterball, also known as Vaan Irai Kal and Krishna\'s Gigantic Butterball, is a gigantic granite boulder resting on a short incline in the historical coastal resort town of Mamallapuram in Tamil Nadu state of India. Being part of the Group of Monuments at Mamallapuram, it is a UNESCO World Heritage Site built during the seventh- and 8th CE as Hindu religious monuments by the Pallava dynasty. It is listed as a protected national monument by the ASI.', 'krishnas-butterball', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(349, 1, 501, 4620, NULL, 'Ramakrishna Temple | Pilgrim Centre | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Ramakrishna Temple, temples in tamil nadu, tamilnadu tourism, ', 'The Ramakrishna Temple in Chennai is the first branch centre of the Ramakrishna Order in Southern India. It was established in 1897 by Swami Ramakrishnananda, one of the direct disciples of Ramakrishna.', 'ramakrishna-temple', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(350, 1, 502, 4636, NULL, 'Santhome Cathedral and Basilica | Pilgrim Centres | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Santhome Cathedral and Basilica, St. Thomas Cathedral Basilica and National Shrine of Saint Thomas, San Thome Church , pilgrim centres in tamil nadu, tamil nadu tourism, tamil nadu churches, chennai churches\r\n', 'With its white texture and tall spires, the Santhome Church stands majestically and makes you pause and appreciate its beauty. Built in neo-Gothic style, the church delights every visitor with its naturally lit interiors, rows of wooden pews and striking windows with coloured panes.', 'santhome-cathedral-and-basilica', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(351, 1, 503, 4650, NULL, 'Pancha Rathas | Mahabalipuram | World Heritage Site | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Pancha Rathas, Mahabalipuram, World Heritage Site, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Pancha Rathas, also known as Five Rathas or Pandava Rathas, is a monument complex at Mahabalipuram in Chengalpet District of Tamil Nadu in India. The complex is under the auspices of the Archaeological Survey of India (ASI) and is part of the UNESCO World Heritage site inscribed by UNESCO as Group of Monuments at Mahabalipuram.', 'pancha-rathas', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(352, 1, 504, 4663, NULL, 'India Seashell Museum | Mahabalipuram | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'India Seashell Museum, Mahabalipuram, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'India Seashell Museum is a popular tourist attraction at Mahabalipuram in Chengalpet District of Tamil Nadu. The museum houses more than 2300 species of shells and nearly 40000 exhibits.', 'india-seashell-museum', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(353, 1, 505, 4677, NULL, 'Mahishasuramardini Cave Temple | Mahabalipuram | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Mahishasuramardini Cave Temple, Mahabalipuram, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'The Mahishasuramardini Cave temple is located very near to a lighthouse at Mahabalipuram in Chengalpet District of Tamil Nadu. The cave temple is dedicated to commemorate the mythological episode where Goddess Durga killed the demon Mahishasura. This particular carving is considered one of best creations of the Pallava Period.', 'mahishasuramardini-cave-temple', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(354, 1, 506, 4690, NULL, 'The Tiger Cave Temple | Mahabalipuram | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'The Tiger Cave Temple, Mahabalipuram, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'The Tiger Cave Temple is a rock-cut Hindu temple complex located in the hamlet of Saluvankuppam near Mahabalipuram in Chengalpet District in Tamil Nadu, India.The Tiger Cave is considered to be one of the Mahabalipuram rock-cut temples constructed by the Pallavas in the 8th century AD. ', 'tiger-cave-temple', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(355, 1, 507, 4703, NULL, 'The Sculpture Museum | Mahabalipuram | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'The Sculpture Museum, Mahabalipuram, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'The Sculpture Museum at Mahabalipuram in Chengalpet District of Tamil Nadu is exclusively dedicated to sculptures and houses more than 3000 of them. Most of the sculptures are that of Gods and Goddesses, and these highlight the astounding art of the Gupta Period. Buddhist and Hindu sculptures are also present in the sculpture museum.', 'mahabalipuram-sculpture-museum', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(356, 1, 508, 4716, NULL, 'The Lighthouse Heritage Museum | Mahabalipuram | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'The Lighthouse Heritage Museum, Mahabalipuram, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'The Lighthouse Heritage Museum in Mahabalipuram at Chengalpet District in Tamil Nadu is a popular tourist attraction. The museum consists of all kinds of heritage items from the old lighthouses of Mahabalipuram and other items related to the same. ', 'the lighthouse heritage museum', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(357, 1, 510, 4739, NULL, 'Upper Bhavani Lake | Destinations | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Upper Bhavani Lake, bhavani lake, upper bhavani dam, places to visit in ooty, kodaikanal, tourist destinations in the nilgiris, the nilgiris, visit tamil nadu, tamil nadu tourism,\r\n', 'Disturbed only by the calls and dances of the wild fauna in the Nilgiri Biosphere reserve, Upper Bhavani Lake is an ideal spot to pick as a destination for a light trek through the woods with friends or family and set camp for the whole day. The lake and the surrounding woods offer a great opportunity to admire the raw beauty of nature up-close.', 'upper-bhavani-lake', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(358, 1, 511, 4755, NULL, 'Emerald Lake | Destinations | Tamil Nadu Tourism ', 'Emerald Lake, the nigiris, places to visit in ooty, ooty tourism, ooty tourist destinations, lakes in tamil nadu, destinations in tamil nadu, tamil nadu tourism, \r\n', 'Emerald lake is set in the backdrop of rising peaks of the Nilgiris and misty tea plantations is a perfect spot to enjoy the sunrise and sunset. Ideal for a day of relaxation with friends or family, Emerald Lake will treat you with a gorgeous landscape and the calmness of the wilderness, where you can be at one with nature the whole day.', 'emerald-lake', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(359, 1, 512, 4771, NULL, 'Rameswaram Beach | Beaches | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'rameswaram beach, beaches in rameswaram, tamil nadu tourism, beaches in tamil nadu, agnitheertham , dhanushkodi, visit rameswaram, rameswaram tourism, rameshwaram, pamban beach', 'Pamban beach is a quiet beach that offers tranquil views of the beach, fishing boats sailing away and the nearby islands. It is located at the beginning of the Indira Gandhi road bridge or the Pamban road bridge.', 'rameswaram-beach', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(360, 1, 513, 4788, NULL, 'Pamban Bridge | Destinations | Tamil Nadu', 'Pamban Bridge, pampan paalam, tamil nadu tourism, places to visist in tamil nadu, tamil nadu tourism, ', 'Considered to be the longest bridge in India constructed over the bay, the Pamban rail bridge used to be the only link between Rameswaram and the mainland until 1988 after which a road bridge was built parallel to it.', 'pamban-bridge', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(361, 1, 514, 4806, NULL, 'Panchamukhi Hanuman temple | Temples in Rameswaram | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Panchamukhi Hanuman temple, temples in rameswaram, ramanathapuram, rameswaram tourism, visit rameswaram, \r\n', 'The Panchamukhi Hanuman temple or five-faced Hanuman temple is dedicated to Lord Hanuman and is seen adorned with Senthooram or vermillion. The idol is depicted with five faces as Lord Hanuman is believed to have revealed his five faces here. The idol has Lord Hanuman in the middle along with the faces of Lord Narasimha, Lord Adivaraha, Lord Garuda and Lord Hayagriva on his sides.', 'panchamukhi-hanuman-temple', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(362, 1, 515, 4823, NULL, 'Pazhamudhir Solai | Pilgrim Centres | Tamil Nadu', 'Pazhamudhir Solai, madurai, temples, plgrim centres in tamil nadu, tamil nadu tourism\r\n', 'At Pazhamudir Solai, Lord Muruga is worshiped along with Goddess Valli and Deivayanai. Legend has it that Muruga tested the famous Tamil poet Avvaiyar when she rested in the shade of a tree near the temple. She had become tired after walking for long hours in the hot sun. Lord Muruga took the guise of a young boy and appeared in front of her. They then indulged in an intelligent interplay of words.', 'pazhamudhir-solai', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(363, 1, 516, 4842, NULL, 'Mahabalipuram Beach | Beaches | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Mahabalipuram Beach, mahabalipuram, mammalapuram, beaches in tamilnadu, tamil nadu tourism, chennai, ', 'Located about 58 km away from Chennai, Mahabalipuram Beach is a perfect choice for beach lovers. Located along the east coast, the beach offers the best that the Bay of Bengal shores offer tourists. Thanks to the amazing sun, sand and water experiences, Mahabalipuram Beach is visited by millions of tourists annually.', 'mahabalipuram-beach', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(364, 1, 517, 4859, NULL, 'Ariyaman Beach | Beaches in Rameswaram | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Ariyaman Beach, beaches in tamil nadu, rameswaram, beaches in rameswaram, tamil nadu tourism, tourist places in rameswaram, visit rameswaram, khushi beach, \r\n', 'Ariyaman Beach is located about 21 km away from the town of Rameswaram, yet carries with it the quaint and poetic feel of the temple town. A place of great significance in history, the beach and the town offers tourists the best of both the experiences.', 'ariyaman-beach', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(365, 1, 518, 4876, NULL, 'Olaikuda Beach | Beaches in Rameswaram  | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Olaikuda Beach, beaches in tamil nadu, rameswaram, rameswaram tourism, beaches in ramanathapuram, places to visit in rameswaram, rameshwaram, tamil nadu tourism, \r\n', 'A placid fishing town in the east coast of Tamil Nadu, Olaikuda is where you can feel time standing still. The Olaikuda beach is one spot that enhances the poetic beauty of the village. Engulfed with splendiferous coral reefs, the sea in this region proffers a visitor many unique sights. ', 'olaikuda-beach', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
