(375, 1, 528, 5039, NULL, 'Gandamana Parvatham | Rameswaram | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'gandamana parvatham, rameswaram tourism, places to visit in rameswaram, Rama Theertham, ramanathapuram, rameswaram tourism, ', 'The Gandamana Parvatham also known as Rama Theertham is one of the pristine religious destinations in Rameswaram where devotees flock in great numbers as the place has notable significance in the Indian epic Ramayana. \r\n', 'gandamana-parvatham', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(376, 1, 529, 5056, NULL, 'Villoondi Theertham  | Rameswaram | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'villoondi theertham , rameswaram, rameshwaram tourism, places to visitin rameswaram, ramanathapuram tourism, tourist places in dhanushkodi, tamil nadu tourism, ', 'Villoondi Theertham is one of those eye-pleasing beaches in Rameswaram that has a quaint and charming quality to it, favoured by most travellers. It is also one of the 64 Theerthas (sacred water bodies) in Rameswaram.\r\n', 'villoondi-theertham', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(377, 1, 530, 5073, NULL, 'Sirumalai | Hill Stations | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'sirumalai, dindigul, hill stations in tamil nadu, tamil ndu tourism, places to visit in tamil nadu, ', 'Are you someone who loves those hairpin curves? Go on an 18-hairpin drive to explore the calmness and silence of lush green forests at Sirumalai. The place with its dense forest along with its mythological relevance is a weekend getaway for the people in Dindigul and Madurai.\r\n', 'sirumalai', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(378, 1, 531, 5090, NULL, 'Vivekananda House and Museum | Museums in Chennai | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'vivekananda house and museum, Vivekanandar Illam, vivekananthands house, vivekananda museum, places to visit in chennai, chennai tourism, tamil nadu tourism, ', 'Vivekananda House or Vivekanandar Illam in Chennai played a significant part in the spread of Ramakrishna Movement in South India. Swami Vivekananda stayed here for nine days, in 1897, after his return from the West.', 'vivekananda-house-and-museum', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(379, 1, 532, 5110, NULL, 'Mudaliar Cuisine | Tamil Nadu Delicacies | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'Mudaliar Cuisine, Tamil Nadu Delicacies, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'The heirloom traditional Mudaliar recipes are from the Vellore region. Their recipes are predominantly rich in vegetables. The ingredients are generally locally sourced and simple but the flavours are beautifully complex with combinations of vegetables.', 'mudaliar-cuisine', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(380, 1, 533, 5120, NULL, 'Tamil Sahibu Cuisine | Tamil Muslim Cuisine | Tamil Nadu Tourism ', 'tamil sahibu cuisine, Tamil Muslim Cuisine, Tamil Nadu Tourism ', 'Intermingling of Arab traders and the local women during eight or ninth century resulted in formation of Tamil Sahibu Cuisine or Tamil Muslim Cuisine near the coastal towns of Tamil Nadu like Kilakarai, Kayalpatnam etc.', 'tamil-sahibu-cuisine', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(381, 1, 534, 5128, NULL, 'Cuisines of the Tamil Land | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'cuisines of the tamil land, Tamil Nadu tourism, tamil regional cuisine', 'The delectable cuisine of Tamil Nadu is a culinary style which dates to antiquity and has since influenced the other states of South and South-East Asia. ', 'cuisines-of-the-tamil-land', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(382, 1, 535, 5134, NULL, 'Tamil Regional cuisine | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'explore the regional cuisine of tamil nadu, Tamil Nadu tourism', 'Next time you visit Tamil Nadu explore beyond idli, vada and sambar. Instead savour each regional cuisine that boasts of unique cooking methods and spices. They have been backed with heirloom family recipes, ancient culture and traditions, community history and external influences.', 'explore-the-regional-cuisine-of-tamil-nadu', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(383, 1, 536, 5144, NULL, 'Sweet Savouries from Tamil Nilam | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'sweet savouries from tamil Nilam, Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'No meal can be treated as complete without the desserts. The indulgent desserts of Tamil Nadu are exquisite and nutritious. Most are healthy preparations using less sugar and include healthy proteins like green gram and chickpea.', 'sweet-savouries-from-tamil-nilam', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(384, 1, 537, 5153, NULL, 'Darasuram | A relic of bygone Chola power & prosperity | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'a relic of bygone chola power & prosperity, Tamil Nadu tourism\r\n', 'The great Chola king, Rajaraja II (1143 CE â1173 CE), built the Airavatesvara Temple in Darasuram, which is ranked only third after the two famed Chola temples of Thanjavur and Gangaikondacholapuram.', 'darasuram-a-relic-of-bygone-chola-power-prosperity', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(385, 1, 538, 5158, NULL, 'Explore the Surreal Kolli Hills  | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'explore the surreal kolli hills, Tamil Nadu tourism, Namakkal district, hiking in Tamil Nadu, adventure tourism in Tamil Nadu', 'Dazzling through the woods on top of hills of the Eastern ghats is the road that bends the most. Located in the high altitudes of the Eastern ghats, the Kolli Hills derive their name from the Goddess who guards the hills-ettukai Amman, also called the Kollipavai. Run wild and free in the unrevealed greenery.', 'explore-the-surreal-kolli-hills', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
