(388, 1, 541, 5192, NULL, 'Nettukuppam Beach | Beaches in Chennai | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'nettukuppam beach, beaches in chennai, tamil nadu tourism, chennai tourism, places to visit in chennai,', 'Away from the madding city crowd, nestling in a tranquil setting, lies a quiet beach that would mesmerise any visitor. Nettukuppam beach might not be a part of popular hype, but worth every visit you make. Come, be embraced by serenity.\r\n', 'nettukuppam-beach', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(389, 1, 542, 5213, NULL, 'Theeyal | Recipes | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'theeyal, nanjil nadu cuisine, tamil nadu foor varities, tamil recipes, tamil cuisine, food varities of tamilnadu, tamil nadu special theeyal, Kondaikadalai Theeyal, Chickpea Theeyal', 'Kondaikadalai Theeyal or Chickpea Theeyal is a flavoursome curry from Nanjil Nadu cuisine. Most recipes from this land are known for their generous use of coconut, Theeyal being no exception. The roasted coconut in the curry brings in a distinct flavour that is accentuated by the chickpeas added to it. The speciality of the Theeyal is that the chickpeas added here can be replaced with drumstick, brinjals, onions or garlic, each of which never fails to bring out the authentic flavour of the curry', 'theeyal', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(390, 1, 543, 5221, NULL, 'Government Museum, Chennai | Museums | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'government museum, chennai, museums in chennai, chennai tourism, tamil nadu tourism, museums, places to visit in chennai, visit tamil nadu, ', 'Started in 1851, Government Museum, Chennai, or Madras Museum is the second oldest museum in India after the Indian Museum in Kolkata. Rich in archaeological and numismatic collections, the museum has the largest collection of Roman antiquities outside Europe.', 'government-museum-chennai', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
(391, 1, 544, 5238, NULL, 'Thiruvalluvar Kottam | Monuments | Tamil Nadu Tourism', 'thiruvalluvar kottam, museums, monuments in chennai, places to visit in chennai, chennai tourism, tamil nadu tourism', 'A memorial monument of noted Tamil poet and philosopher Thiruvalluvar (commonly known as Valluvar) who wrote the famous Thirukkural, a collection of couplets. The couplets on ethics, politics, economy and love are considered an exceptional and widely cherished work of Tamil literature.', 'thiruvalluvar-kottam', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 1),
